title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat the prepared mustard, mixed with red currant jelly.
Add the frankfurters and heat through.
Serve hot from a chafing dish, electric frying pan, crock-pot or shallow saucepan.
Spear with toothpicks to eat.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill overnight.
Serve with rye bread.

title: potatoes, sausage and green beans
directions: Put potatoes in large pan. Add green beans with juice and top with sausage.
Cover pan. Cook on medium heat until potatoes are soft. Add salt and pepper. Serve.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except last two, and put in greased 8 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with drained cornflakes and almonds. Refrigerate overnight and bake uncovered at 350° next day.

title: double pineapple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large bowl combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg, oil, brown sugar and cinnamon (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 up the sides of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spicy chicken salad
directions: Bake the chicken after you sprinkle the seasoning on it for about 20 to 30 minutes, covered, at 325°.
In a medium size bowl, combine all of the other ingredients.
Remove the cooked chicken and chop into cubes.
Fold it into the dressing mixture.
Chill about 30 minutes.
This is great served with nonfat saltine crackers or on a sandwich.
It can also be served on a lettuce leaf with some fresh fruit.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs first.
Add flour, sugar and salt; mix.
Add milk and butter.
Stir a little more.
Add corn.
Stir.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: wheat-free pancakes
directions: *Oat flour:
You can grind from oatmeal in blender.

title: springtime salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Chill until soft set. Beat cream cheese and banana together.
Fold in jello.
Add whipped cream, pineapple, nuts, cherries and marshmallows.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: "cole" slaw
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add Kraft cole slaw dressing to taste.

title: honey garlic pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork; pour chops in heavy plastic bag, seal.
Refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Prepare covered grill with drip pan in center, banked by medium hot coals.
Remove chops from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill chops 16 minutes, turning one and basting occasionally with reserved marinade; or broil chops 5 inches from heat source for 13 to 18 minutes, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: paella
directions: In a large kettle, brown chicken pieces well in the olive oil over medium-high heat.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Discard any fat in pan.
Add chorizos and bacon to pan and cook, stirring until lightly browned.
Add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring, until soft.
Add the rice and saffron to pan and stir until rice is lightly browned (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, parsley, vinegar, wine, oregano, coriander, paprika and salt to the pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
(Can be refrigerated for up to a day before cooking.)
Cover and bring mixture to boiling over medium heat, stirring as necessary. Simmer until chicken and rice are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until shrimp are firm and pink.
Remove from heat.
With tongs, remove chicken pieces and set aside; keep warm.
Stir peas and smoked clams or oysters into rice mixture.
If desired, transfer to a wide, deep serving platter.
Arrange chicken around rice and seafood mixture.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes in round pans or 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon, drain off fat from bacon and onions.
Add potatoes and water.
Boil until done.
Stir in soup and sour cream. Gradually add milk and remaining ingredients.
Do not boil.
Makes a big pot.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Combine onion, egg, milk, applesauce, sage, pepper and salt; add seasoned stuffing croutons.
Let stand 5 minutes or until croutons are soft.
Mix until smooth.
Then combine with ground chuck.
Shape into meatballs and place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add baking soda and flour.
Add full can crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with Cream Cheese Icing while it is still hot.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes, onion rings, water and butter in a 2-quart casserole dish with cover.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes covered until potatoes are tender, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain if necessary.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and cover to allow cheese to melt.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peaches 'n' cream
directions: Combine in a bowl the butter, milk, baking powder, flour, egg, pudding mix and juice from drained peaches.
Mix until smooth. Pour into oblong baking dish.
Place drained peaches on top of mixture. Whip softened cream cheese and sugar. Spread on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread 'n butter pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers (thinly).
Set aside.
Peel and slice onions (thinly).
In large refrigerator tray, layer cucumbers, onions, salt, cucumbers, onions, salt, cucumbers, onions and salt (this is 3 layers).
Cover tray with foil and place in refrigerator overnight.
In a large pot, pour 1 quart vinegar, 1 pint water, sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add mustard and celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Drain fluid from cucumbers and onions.
Pour into pot mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Into 8 pint jars which have been filled with scalding water, empty one and fill.
Seal each individually until all 8 jars are filled and sealed.
Keep in a dark place.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and pecans.
Pecans can be toasted.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Place in 9 x 13 pan and chill until firm.
Keeps in refrigerator about 2 weeks.

title: vanilla peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, vanilla and milk until soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix and pour into buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown sirloin, bacon and onion. Drain well. Stir in beans. Combine ketchup, vinegar, salt and brown sugar.
Pour over beans. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Shred lettuce in bottom of large Pyrex dish or flat salad bowl.
Layer spinach on top of lettuce.
Mix celery, onions, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread these on top of the spinach.
Mix equal parts of sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over chopped ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over the dressing and bacon bits on top of cheese.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 4 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bottom of 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers, banana slices and vanilla pudding; spread to the edges, smoothing well. Do this again with remaining wafer, bananas and pudding.
(Save a banana for the top and a few vanilla wafers), then end with whipped cream and top with bananas and wafers.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Boil the cabbage leaves in boiling water 4 to 5 minutes and drain.

title: swedish spritz cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and extract.
Fill cookie press.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 35\0° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken with sausage and mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients in shallow 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May use sweet sausage or 1/2 hot and 1/2 sweet.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour into stuffing.
Line bottom and sides of casserole dish with 1/2 of mixture.
Mix all other ingredients with mashed squash.
Pour into casserole dish over stuffing. Sprinkle other stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cornmeal.
Add eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: big wheel sandwich loaf(serves 8)
directions: Slice bread horizontally into 6 equal layers using an electric or serrated knife.
Spread horseradish on first layer and top with roast beef and second bread layer.
Spread mayonnaise on second layer and top with Swiss cheese and third bread layer.
Spread mustard on third layer and top with ham and four bread layer. Cover fourth layer with tomato slices, bacon and fifth bread layer.
Top fifth bread layer with American cheese, onion and remaining bread layer.

title: creamed cabbage(stuet kaal)
directions: Cut cabbage medium fine and boil in salted water until barely tender.
Melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour to a smooth paste.
Pour in milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly. Boil 5 to 6 minutes and salt to taste.
Grate nutmeg into sauce and add drained cabbage.
Stir and heat thoroughly.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Pour 1/2 cup cold V-8 juice in container.
Sprinkle gelatin on top.
Heat remainder of V-8 juice, pour in and stir.
Refrigerate just until mixture begins to harden.
Fold in any additional ingredients such as chopped nuts, chopped celery, olives, etc. Either top with slices of hard-boiled eggs or spread Miracle Whip on top.
Cut into squares and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Congeals quickly!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Puree the tomatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, red pepper sauce, salt and pepper in a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Add the scallions and pulse twice.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 2 cups.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Brown, crumble and drain hamburger.
Follow the directions on the Rice-A-Roni package for browning the rice.
When the rice is browned, add to the hamburger.
Add 2 cups water; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle any desired amount of grated cheese over the mixture.
Cover and simmer until the cheese is melted.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix.
Pour mixture into greased and floured pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This pie forms its own crust as it bakes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and add a few drops of hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into ball and cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake until brown on top or about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered pan, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp cocktail with chili hot sauce
directions: Combine ingredients except for shrimp.
Chill thoroughly. Serve in individual cocktail cups.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add salt and flour, blending well. Divide into 2 parts.
Roll each part into thin strips.
Cut into small pieces and let dry.
Cook in broth until tender.
Can use chicken, turkey or beef broth.
Add meat, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into deep casserole dish.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour evenly over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Top should be brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix crab meat, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Fill mushroom caps.
Place in casserole dish with lid in oven safe dish.
Cover with melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes on 375°. Remove and place under broiler for a few seconds to lightly brown. Remove from oven.
Spoon excess butter over mushrooms if desired.

title: zippy hot appetizers
directions: Brown one package brown and serve sausages and cut into bite size squares.
Mix together brown sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add vinegar, pineapple juice and water.
Cook together until thickened. Add sausages, pineapple, cherries and green peppers.
Place in chafing dish and keep warm while being served.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Beat until fairly smooth.
Bake in 8-inch pan in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate dazzle
directions: Blend together crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly into the bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon over crumbs.
Set in freezer while whipping cream.
Gently fold mini marshmallows into whipping cream.
Sprinkle crushed peppermint on top.
Freeze.
Serves 9.

title: chicken rice dinner(one dish meal)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken pieces.
In skillet (medium heat), brown chicken in oil.
Place rice in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (ungreased).
Sprinkle with onions, top with mushrooms.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and pour over all.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken pieces run clear and rice is tender. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with "Marinated Garden Salad." Serves 5.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cut steak into serving-size pieces. Trim fat and discard.
Coat each piece with flour.
Lightly brown.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cocoa fudge cookies
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter or margarine with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour mixture alternately with coffee, beginning with flour.
Add vanilla.
Drop onto lightly greased baking sheet with teaspoon.
Bake about 8 minutes at 325°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening with fork.
Add salt and buttermilk. Shake some flour on waxed paper and pat out dough about an inch thick. Cut out biscuits with a plastic drinking glass for whatever size you want.
Bake in a greased pan at 350 until done.

title: salad
directions: Dissolve the cream cheese in the boiling water with the jello. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour in glass 8 x 12-inch dish. Chill.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces and put in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer rest of the ingredients in order.
Mix the sugar with the mayo and spread over the top of the salad like a frosting. Then top with cheese.
Let refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
You can top with a little parsley if you desire.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two (9-inch) layer cake pans. Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add corn oil, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Fold in walnuts, carrots and pineapple.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Add grated cheese and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: curried beef and rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together the water, onion, carrot, bouillon granules, curry powder and garlic.
Heat to boiling, then stir in rice.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir beef, peas and tomato into rice mixture.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes more or until rice and peas are tender.
Make 4 servings.

title: apple hermit cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in nuts, dates, apples and rolled oats.
Add flour and cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Spread pie filling evenly over bottom of pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pie filling and drizzle with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an iron skillet with Pam and add 1 tablespoon oil.
Place skillet in oven while mixing ingredients. Combine corn bread mix, Bisquick mix, salt, egg, evaporated milk, water and 3 tablespoons oil.
Pour into skillet and bake until browned, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and mix in.
Add pumpkin and beat all together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, 2/3 cup of sugar and flavoring until smooth and lemon colored.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan greased heavily with butter.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes; cool for 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add sherbet.
Stir until melted.
Stir in oranges.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add apples and nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients, add to apple mixture. Do not use an electric mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hr and 20 min.

title: sweet and sour low calorie dressing
directions: Combine ingredients for a green salad.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: crab cakes with shrimp
directions: Pick over the crab to remove any cartilage or shell.
Leave the lumps as large as possible.
Shell and devein the shrimp.
Put the shrimp in a food processor or blender and add the egg, cream, salt and pepper.
Blend as finely as possible.
Pour and scrape the mixture into a mixing bowl.
Add the crab, green onions, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Blend gently but thoroughly.
Shape the mixture into 10 cakes.

title: cranberry pork roast in slow-cooker
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brown derby cobb salad
directions: Chop finely the lettuce, watercress, chicory and romaine and arrange them in the salad bowl.
Cut the tomatoes in half, remove the seeds, then dice them finely and arrange them over the chopped greens.
Chop the bacon finely and sprinkle over the salad.
Cut the avocado in small pieces and place them around the edge of the salad.
Decorate the salad by sprinkling over the top the chopped eggs, chopped chives and crumbled cheese.
Just before serving, mix the salad thoroughly with Old Fashioned French Dressing.

title: run for the roses pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, butter, eggs, bourbon and vanilla in bowl.
Beat until blended.
Stir in
chocolate
morsels and nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: margo's homemade mustard
directions: In small bowl, stir together mustard and 4 teaspoons of cold water.
Set aside.
In 1-quart saucepan, mix rest of ingredients well.
Cook over low heat for about 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard mixture until smooth.
Cover in tight container.
Refrigerate.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Spread cracker mixture over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar and butter in large saucepan.
Heat to lukewarm.
Remove from heat and add yeast.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Stir in flour and everything else (except
cheese and ground beef)
Stir until mixed well. Knead on floured board.
Roll onto greased pan.
Top with ground beef and cheese.
Cook until done.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush Doritos (fun for the kids!).
Preheat oven to 375°. Brown beef and drain fat.
Mix in sauces and kidney beans (undrained).
In a large, covered, deep Pyrex dish, place a layer of crushed chips, then meat sauce, then top with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese and crushed Doritos.
Serve with dinner rolls and side salad.

title: never fail coffee cake
directions: In a 7 x 11-inch pan, put the oleo.
Place in 350° oven and let it melt.
Take out of oven.
Beat sugar and egg until light yellow. Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Grease pan and pour oleo into batter.
Pour batter into pan; sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruit, nut and rice casserole
directions: Cover apricots and raisins with water and soak for 1/2 hour. Boil rice according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a skillet, melt butter and saute onion, green peppers, curry powder.
Add in almonds and the drained, chopped apricots and raisins and the cooked rice.
CORRECT THE SEASONING and put into a greased baking dish to bake for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a ball.
Use reserved cup of nuts for rolling cheese ball in.

title: mommy's chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until done.
Put in jars and seal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except cheese.
Put in oblong baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; top with slices of favorite cheese.
Return, uncovered, to oven for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and corn.
Mix with other ingredients.
Top with Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basil snow peas and tomatoes
directions: Wash snow pea pods; trim ends and remove any tough strings. Set aside.
Place butter in a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave at High 45 seconds, or until melted.
Add snow peas, chopped onion, soy sauce, basil and salt; toss gently.
Cover; microwave at High 3 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes, stirring gently.
Cover; microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and water.
Mix well.
Add the grated cheese and nuts.
Chill.

title: sweet onion cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until transparent.
Stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Set aside.
Combine cornmeal, sugar and dill.
Combine eggs, corn, milk, oil and hot sauce.
Add egg mixture to cornmeal mixture all at once and blend.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 9-inch square pan or dish.
Spread onion mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
An unusual combination.

title: tuna shimi
directions: Mix horseradish, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper. Pour over tuna and mix lightly. Place on spinach leaves. Sprinkle with scallions and lemon juice. Add radishes. Chill until serving time.

title: lazy woman's belly stickers
directions: Thaw bread dough in refrigerator or on countertop until room temperature.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Roll into balls and place in pie pan with 1/4 inch in between.
Allow to rise until balls are touching.
Mix cinnamon and Eagle Brand; pour evenly over all pans of belly stickers.

title: cheese tartlets
directions: Line large muffin pans with papers.
Place one wafer in each. Beat cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool and chill.
At serving time, place spoonful of fruit filling on each.
Top with a dollop of Cool Whip, if desired.
Makes 18.

title: divinity(candy)
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in heavy saucepan.
Cook and do not stir until syrup forms soft ball stage when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Pour slowly into egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until candy holds shape and loses gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain well. Saute onions in oleo.
Add broccoli, soup, cheese, mushrooms, water chestnuts, 3/4 cup of almonds and 1/2 cup of bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 (1-quart) casserole dishes (or its equivalent). Top with remaining almonds and crumbs.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: quick chicken
directions: Use a small bowl to mix yogurt, dried onion, dehydrated chicken broth and sherry.
Arrange chicken in a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Cover with sliced mushrooms and yogurt mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for about 25 minutes or until fork can be inserted with ease. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Add salsa; cook for 10 minutes, covered, and 3 minutes, uncovered.
Spoon into tortillas; top with cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Best if served with refried beans.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Put on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: e-z luckshun kugel *
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water, then drain.
Beat eggs and add them to the noodles.
Season to taste.
Mix all of the ingredients together (or layer, if desired).
Put into a buttered 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers or cereal.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned on top.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, eggs, onion and salt.
Form into small balls.
Brown in skillet or oven.
Pour off fat.
Mix together chili sauce, jelly and juice.
Pour over balls and simmer 1 hour or cook in crock pot.

title: cottage-cheddar puff
directions: In blender container, combine cheeses, egg yolks, onion, mustard and Worcestershire.
Process until smooth; set aside.
Mix egg whites until stiff; fold into cheese mixture.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo until celery is done.
Add soup and water.
Add Cheez Whiz, rice and broccoli.
Bring to boil. Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana-rum pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix and gelatin.
Cook according to pudding package mix except use the 2 1/4 cups milk.
Remove from heat; pour into a bowl.
Cover surface with clear plastic wrap.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake as per instructions on the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake is cool, using a chopstick punch about 36 holes on top of the cake (approximately 1 to 1 1/2-inches apart). Use caution not to punch holes completely through the cake.
Use a small funnel to fill holes with liquid jello (approximately 1 teaspoon.) Refrigerate cake approximately 1/2 hour to set jello. Top cake with vanilla pudding, then with Cool Whip.
Serves 24.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients except bacon and place in a 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Place bacon on top and bake for 1 hour or until onion and bell pepper are tender at 350°.

title: granny's salad dressing for apples or bananas
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
This was my great-grandmother's recipe.
Now a family tradition.

title: string bean oregonal
directions: Cook string beans as desired (boil, steam, microwave, etc.); set aside.
In a large saucepan over low heat, heat butter and oil.
Add the crushed garlic and peppercorns.
Add remaining ingredients except the cheese.
Mix well and heat until it just begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Add beans, mixing thoroughly.
Place on a warm serving dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the string beans and serve.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, dump in pie filling and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Scatter nuts on top, if desired.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: everlasting apple muffins
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour that has been mixed well with spices, soda and salt.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake muffins at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tipsy cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave at Medium 12 to 13 minutes, stirring once. Stir in brandy and walnuts. Cool. Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sugar-free applesauce-raisin cake
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: never fail fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and beat until creamy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pans.
Place apple slices in pans.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm and if desired with light cream or ice cream.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Set ice cream out to soften. Crush shortbread cookies; mix with soft butter. Press into a glass 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding with milk until thick (will be very thick). Fold ice cream into pudding mixture. (Mix by hand; if electric mixer is used, mixture will become soupy.) Spread mixture on top of shortbread crust and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. While refrigerating, crush Heath bars. Before serving, top with Cool Whip and Heath bar pieces.

title: beef bar-b-q
directions: Cut
beef
into
5 or 6 chunks.
Place in Dutch oven or roaster.
Combine
all
other
ingredients
and
pour over the meat.
Heat to boiling on top of the range.
Cover and bake at 300° for
6 hours or until meat is tender enough to shred with a fork.
Remove
fat
and
bone and pull the meat into shreds with a fork.
If sauce is too "soupy", cook until thick enough to spoon onto buns.
Makes enough for 30 to 40 servings.

title: bubba's jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Drain pineapple. Add to Jell-O. Add bananas and frozen strawberries. Mix well. Pour half of mixture in dish. Refrigerate until firm. Spread sour cream on top of this. Pour remaining mixture on top of sour cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs.
Mash them with potato masher.
Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Boil until fork can go into potato.
Drain. Add eggs, diced onions, relish, salad dressing, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well, then add potatoes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Cover with boiling water (amount as you like it).
Leave onion whole and put the 3 cloves into the onion.
Chop the other onion and put all ingredients in with the meat.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and leave in refrigerator for 2 days.
When ready to eat, skim fat off and add potatoes and carrots.

title: blueberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water. Stir in fruit cocktail and juice.
Let set.

title: picante potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture is set and golden brown.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with bacon.
Continue baking 5 minutes.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix the sugar, water and syrup; cook until it will spin a thread.
Have 2 egg whites beaten stiff.
Slowly pour 1/2 of hot mixture into the egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook the other 1/2 of syrup mixture until it will harden when a small amount is dropped into cold water.
Slowly add to egg white mixture; beat until creamy.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies(no flour)
directions: Mix all ingredients well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful and squash flat on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for exactly 13 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen, depending on size of cookies.

title: southwestern corn chowder
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine ham, cream-style corn, whole kernel corn and green chilies (drained if necessary).
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture just comes to a boil (2 to 3 minutes).
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in sour cream and milk; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (3 to 4 minutes). Do not allow the chowder to boil. Makes 6 servings.
Per serving:
230 calories, 7 g fat.

title: venison pepper steak
directions: Chop pepper and onions.
Flour meat and fry all together until meat is brown.
After meat is browned, add canned tomatoes and tomato sauce.
If too thick, add a couple cups of water.
Cook and stir for approximately 30 minutes.
Finally, add pepper and salt to taste.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in small skillet; add onion and cook until transparent.
Combine onion, biscuit mix, parsley, egg, 1/2 cup cheese and milk, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 9 servings.

title: nannie's chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together until well blended.
Add milk and mix.
Cook on medium heat and add butter when it starts to boil, stirring often, until a small spoonful dropped into cold water forms a soft ball in your fingers.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat fast, until it starts to thicken.
Then add peanut butter at once.
Blend well and pour into pan greased with butter immediately.
Refrigerate, then cut and serve.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in nectar. Add oil, juice, eggs and cake mix. Beat well; pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 360° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Glaze while hot with 2 cups sifted confectioners sugar and juice of 2 lemons.

title: tarragon-sesame salad dressing
directions: In blender, mix oil, vinegar, salt and honey.
Pour into jar and add sesame seed and tarragon.
Shake well and serve or chill for future use.

title: wiener-bean bake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and stir.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: chocolate tofu ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor or blender until smooth and creamy (it may be necessary to do this in several batches).
Transfer mixture to a half gallon or large electric or hand crank freezer.
Assemble freezer according to manufacturer's directions, using about 4 parts ice to part rock salt.
When electric motor stalls or hand cranking becomes difficult, remove dasher.
Serve immediately, or transfer to a rigid plastic container, cover, and place in freezer for up to 1 month.
Pureed tofu takes the place of egg yolks in this rich tasting but lower calorie ice cream.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: beignets(oreilles de cochon)
directions: Half fill a large, deep saucepan with oil and preheat it to 375°.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon into a large mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg well, then beat in the sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour the egg mixture into the flour and mix slightly until moistened.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll the dough out to a 1/4-inch thickness.
Slice into diamond shapes, about 3 inches long.
Fry in oil, turning once, until they are golden brown and puffed up.
Remove, drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve immediately with cafe' au lait. Yield: about 20 pieces.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Cool completely. Mix together in pan cherry juice, cornstarch dissolved in water, and boil until thick.
Add cherries, sugar and almond flavoring to thickened mixture.
Cool completely.
Whip chilled milk and add to cooled marshmallow mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Pour 1/2 marshmallow mixture in crust.
Put layer of cherry mixture on top. Top it off with rest of marshmallow mix.
Sprinkle few graham cracker crumbs on top and chill thoroughly.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, cream of mushroom soup, milk and seasonings in large bowl.
Gradually stir in Durkee fried dried onions (leave 2 tablespoons for topping sprinkles).
Pour mixture into baking pan previously sprayed with Pam.
Use reserved onion sprinkles for top of mixture.
Dribble margarine over top.

title: baked flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Place fish single layer in pan.
Sprinkle with season.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, uncover.

title: 14 karat cake(carrot cake)
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and mix. Then add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Put into greased layer pan or loaf
pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Takes longer in a loaf pan.

title: pepper relish
directions: Fine grind onions; drain and discard juice by squeezing through cheesecloth.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and ground hot pepper.
Cook together on top of stove until onions are good and done (they will turn pinkish).

title: picante sauce
directions: Core tomatoes and drop in boiling water until the skins crack. Transfer to a bowl of cold water and slip off skins. Chop the chilies, onions, jalapeos, tomatoes and cilantro coarsely. Mix ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve at room temperature.

title: soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut margarine into flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in raisins and just enough buttermilk so dough leaves side of bowl.

title: hot and spicy chili mac
directions: Fry beef, suet and onion together; add spices.
Stir until mixed.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Add water as needed.

title: honey baked beans hawaiian style(serves 48 - three gallons)
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and cover with fresh water. Add salt pork, onions
and
bay
leaves.
Cook	for
1 hour or until beans are
just
tender.
Drain, reserve cooking liquid. Combine honey,
pineapple
juice, vinegar, ketchup, soy sauce, dry mustard and garlic powder.	Mix until blended.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.

title: herb potato wedges
directions: Brush a large piece of heavy duty foil with some butter.
In small bowl, combine butter, oil, onion, parsley, chili powder, basil, salt and pepper.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices (do not peel potatoes).
Place potatoes on foil and brush oil mixture over potatoes.
Tightly seal edges of foil.
Place on grill.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: lemonade punch
directions: Combine all ingredients to make a gallon.

title: malinda's favorite
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Let pasta set for about 5 minutes, then add cheese.
This is a low-cal healthy dish that's very tasty.

title: scrambled eggs with corn
directions: Drain corn and add to melted butter.
Add seasoning and cook 5 minutes over high heat.
Reduce heat.
Add beaten eggs and stir until eggs are cooked through, but still moist.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except ground chuck.
Add the ground chuck to other ingredients and mix together until meat holds together; set aside.
Take plastic oven bag and sprinkle with flour.
Place mixture in bag and seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate velvet pudding pie
directions: Prepare pudding with 1 cup milk as directed on package.
With mixer, slowly blend in chocolate at low speed until smooth.
Then fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in salt, oleo and eggs.
Fold in grated apples.
Put in single crust (unbaked).
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; for 35 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: orange spice tea
directions: Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to hot water.
Sit down and relax.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place dinner rolls on a cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on cooled crust.
Chop up your favorite fresh vegetables and put on the filling.
Top with some Cheddar cheese.

title: jackie's creamy coconut pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and set aside.
Prepare pie filling with 3 1/2 cups milk as directed on package for pie.
Add coconut to filling and cool for about 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour in pie shell and cover with wax paper and chill for 3 hours.
Spread whipped topping over pie and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in mold and freeze.

title: country-style butter biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt with pastry blender in a large bowl until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Cut butter into 1/4-inch pieces.
Toss with flour mixture.
Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and forms a ball.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface, gently roll to coat.
Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 3-inch cutter.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with butter.
Serve.

title: miscellaneous quiche
directions: Bake pie crust 10 minutes and let cool.
Saute onions, pepper and mushrooms and cool.
Fry bacon or ham; let cool, then sprinkle in bottom of pie crust shell along with vegetables.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over bacon (ham) and vegetables; add milk to Egg Beaters and beat.
Pour Egg Beaters and milk mixture over the other ingredients and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stay-in-bed stew
directions: Place stew beef and vegetables in shallow pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and peas (juice, too) thoroughly and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover tightly.
Cook for 5 hours at 250° to 300°.

title: no bake choc-oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine over medium heat in saucepan.
Cook, stirring continually, until it starts to boil. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and salt. Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Cool 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: red cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add coloring and cocoa.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour and salt.
Add vanilla. Dissolve baking soda in vinegar and fold in.
Beat approximately 2 minutes by hand.
Put in greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a lightly greased baking dish.
Add onion, Parmesan cheese and seasonings to taste.
Toss well.
Slice butter over top, cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli classic
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish arrange a layer of bread, chicken, mushrooms, water chestnuts and broccoli.
Dot with butter, combine soups and mayonnaise.
Pour over layers.
Add pimento and cheese to casserole.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine stuffing mix and enough butter to moisten.
Spread over casserole.
Return to oven to brown topping.

title: sweet potato spoon bread
directions: Grate well scrubbed (not peeled) sweet potatoes.
Mix eggs and honey, then add oil.
Mix until smooth.
Add potato, grated orange and lemon peel in this mixture.
Add spices and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
After mixed well, add flour gradually.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until golden.
Bake longer for crisp cookies.

title: pea patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
It should have a texture like pancake batter.
Use a large spoon and drop by spoonfuls onto hot, greased pan, and cook like pancakes.
Cook until crispy.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes until done.

title: texas sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Take out amount as needed. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup with water and pour over rice.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter and lay on top of rice.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Let chill at least 1 hour.

title: chili mac
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in large pan over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble beef.
Drain well.
Wipe pan with paper towel.
Return beef mixture to pan.
Add cooked elbow macaroni and next 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a casserole.
Reserve some onion rings and cheese for topping.
Put remainder of ingredients in casserole. Put onion rings and cheese on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half lengthwise.
Layer ham and cheese.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes. Pour over top of rolls.
Brush over top of rolls.
Seal with foil.
Sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut in quarters.
Cut quarters in 3 strips. Dip in butter, then dip in rest of ingredients.
Place in single layer in greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 400° oven, turning once or twice during baking.

title: delicious beef roast
directions: Wash roast well.
In roasting pan, spread 1 package soup mix evenly over bottom.
Put roast on top.
Sprinkle the other package of soup mix over roast.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over roast.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until roast is tender and the soup is thickened into gravy.
Very good.

title: skor cake
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; stir well.
Add flour and baking powder to this mixture. Add nuts if used.
Spread mixture evenly in greased pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix well and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Serve hot over chocolate cake, covered with vanilla ice cream.
"Good hot fudge cake."

title: la verne fortson's chocolate pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Stir in milk, then egg yolks.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick, stirring almost constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla until margarine melts.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.

title: cauliflower and carrot casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots in water with salt; drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over cooked cauliflower and carrots.
Put in casserole dish.
Blend butter and crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Blend oil and chocolate in bowl, then add sugar.
Blend well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture. Beat eggs in one at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan generously.
Pour in mixture. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cream butter, cheese and pepper until smooth.
Slowly add whipping cream; set aside.
Boil pasta in salt water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain well.
(Don't rinse pasta or pot.) Put back in pot.
Add butter mixture and mix well.
Cover and keep warm until serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
In 1 1/2-quart baking dish or bowl, beat eggs, then add sugar and milk.
Spoon-stir until well blended.
Add rice and spoon-stir again.
Add melted margarine.
If consistency is too thick, add a little more milk.
Taste for sweetness.
Add vanilla and cinnamon; stir thoroughly.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together chicken, pickles, pecans, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Carefully fold in eggs.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on chilled lettuce.
Garnish with tomatoes, sweet pickle and parsley.

title: orange rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
If it seems too dry, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water to moisten. Pour into casserole and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serve with a vegetable, salad and rolls.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Partially defrost hash browns.
Mix ingredients except 1/2 stick margarine and corn flakes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt remaining margarine and mix with corn flakes and spread on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 12.

title: homemade clay dough
directions: Mix in large bowl by hand until pliable.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer salad in large bowl or long dish.
Layer ingredients, one at a time.
Do not toss.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar together, then spread.
Now add cheese.
Now sprinkle crumbled bacon on top. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: broken angel cake with chocolate chips
directions: Melt chocolate chips with water.
Next, beat egg yolks with sugar and fold in chocolate mixture.
Fold in whipping cream. Break cake up into uneven pieces.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the mixture over the cake and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball mex
directions: Mix all the cream cheese and the mild Mexican Velveeta with the onion soup mix and the crushed walnut pieces, after you have crushed them into smaller pieces.
Take the chipped beef or ham and dice into small pieces.
Then add them to the cheese mix, then form it into a ball.
You may sprinkle nuts on the cheese ball if you like.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and put in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork picante
directions: Coat pork cubes with taco seasoning.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook to brown, stirring occasionally.
Add salsa and preserves to pan; lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4. Approximately per serving:
calories 263; fat 10 gm and cholesterol 66 mg.
Serve with hot rice and mixed bean salad.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems from the mushrooms; chop them very fine. Coat the caps with lemon juice.
Remove the sausage meat from the casings; place it in a large bowl.
Mix in the diced mushroom stems and a small amount of salt and pepper.
Blend thoroughly, using a light touch.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spoon the sausage mixture into the mushroom caps, smoothing the tops into a rounded shape.
Butter a baking dish; set the mushrooms in it, sausage side up.
Bake about 15 minutes, or until the sausage meat is cooked through.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley.

title: lois's salad
directions: Combine lettuces, celery, onion and oranges in a large bowl. Heat and crystalize sugar and almonds.
Pour out onto waxed paper. Cool and break apart.
Add to salad.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream. Add remaining ingredients and top with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast shrimp
directions: Fry onion and green pepper in bacon grease. When onion is golden, add shrimp; turn these several times with onion and pepper. Add enough water to make a sauce (about 1 cup). Do not cover shrimp with water or your sauce will be tasteless. Simmer 2 or 3 minutes and thicken with flour and a little water made into a paste.
Add seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup. Cook slowly until thickens. Serve with grits, rice or hominy. Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Add baking powder, soda and flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Cool and cut in 2-inch squares.
Mix pudding with milk.

title: cheddar-potato bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart dish, combine soup, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes until blended.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced green onion, if desired.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla. Melt chocolate and add to sugar mixture. Add 1 beaten egg and beat 5 minutes. Add second egg and beat 5 minutes more. The 10 minutes beating is very important. Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry sponge shortcake
directions: Set oven at 410° to preheat.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift together the salt, baking powder and flour.
Place eggs in mixing bowl and beat vigorously until very thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Fold in flour mixture until well blended.
Fold in vanilla.
Spread in greased pan with spatula.
Bake for 13 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares and top with berries and cream or whipped topping.

title: roast beef casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Put in a large Pyrex dish.
Cook for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Place butter in 3 quart casserole dish.
Heat in microwave oven on full power for one minute, or until melted.
Add chocolate morsels.
Heat in microwave on power level six for 3 1/2 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Cool chocolate enough so that marshmallows will not melt when stirred in.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Allow to stand until stiff enough to form into rolls. Spread coconut on two (2) sheets of wax paper (1 1/2 ft length). Divide mixture in half.
Form in long rolls on coconut.
Coat all sides of rolls evenly with coconut.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
Cut 1/4 to 1/2 inch slices.

title: portuguese linguica casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Saute linguica, onion and green pepper in oil until pepper is cooked. Add tomatoes and cook until bubbly.
Combine macaroni and mixture in casserole dish.
Beat egg and evaporated milk together and pour over casserole.
Cut cheese into small pieces and mix together with casserole ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Heat salad oil in Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Add garlic, carrots, celery and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add broth, vegetable juice, tomatoes, basil, thyme or oregano, salt, pepper and crowder peas.
Bring to a boil and allow mixture to simmer for at least 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is tender.
Serve in soup bowls.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of chowder in soup bowl, if desired.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix chicken broth, vegetable broth, water and bouillon.
Add raw vegetables and spices; cook until tender.
Add rice and Homemade Noodles; cook until tender.
Add Dumplings last and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered, then 10 minutes, covered.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Cook with the bacon and pepper pod until the peas are very tender.
Add rice and salt and pepper to taste. Pour into casserole.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until liquid is absorbed and dish is thoroughly heated.

title: swedish spirits
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with sugar.
Cream butter and add to first mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Use pastry tube to make cookies of various designs.
Bake in moderate oven until light brown at 350°.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: baked tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini in water or chicken broth, al dente. Meanwhile, melt butter and make roux by adding flour and stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Add milk and stock, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.
Add basil and garlic (or pesto), nutmeg and pepper.

title: nita's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jar.
Will keep up to 6 months in refrigerator.
Great for barbecue chicken and beef.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and eggs.
Then add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet, put 1/2 teaspoon filling on dough.
Cover with another 1/2 teaspoon dough. Bake until brown at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together pie filling, crushed pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened over medium heat.
Add jello and let cool.
Add chopped pecans and diced banana.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill and garnish with Cool Whip if desired.

title: artichoke dip 3
directions: Drain hearts well and cut into quarters.
Mix all ingredients and put into a greased 9-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook sugar, juice, butter, flour and egg until thick.
Cool mixture and fold into Cool Whip.
(Two cans of pineapple planks will make enough juice for recipe.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat
together sugar and Wesson oil; add eggs, one at a time, beating
after
each addition.
Sift and measure flour. Add soda, salt and cinnamon, then sift flour mixture together. Add
flour alternately
with chopped apples.
Add vanilla and mix
well.
Add pecans
and
dates.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased
and floured
tube
pan	(10-inch)
at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasticcio
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
While macaroni is cooking, cook and stir hamburger and onion until beef is brown. Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until liquid is almost absorbed, about 8 minutes.
Spread half of macaroni in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with hamburger mixture.
Mix 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese and the nutmeg; sprinkle over beef mixture. Cover with remaining macaroni.

title: roast beef cafe style
directions: Place the roast in a large roasting pan.
Pour the cola beverage over it.
Let it stand for about 10 minutes.
Roast in 425° oven for about 20 minutes per pound.
Salt near the end of the cooking time and check for degree of "doneness" you wish.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in vegetable juice, mushrooms, tomato paste, and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In 13 x 9 inch pan, layer half each of uncooked noodles, meat sauce, ricotta cheese, parmesan, and mozzarella cheese; repeat layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake for another 15 minutes.
Cottage cheese can be substituted for Ricotta Cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour dressing into large bowl and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: meatballs with egg-lemon sauce
directions: Combine first five ingredients, 1 egg, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into meatballs; coat with flour.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 2 1/2 cups water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add meatballs.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid. Beat lemon juice into remaining well beaten eggs.
Add half the hot liquid to egg mixture gradually.
Stir egg mixture into remaining hot liquid.
Pour over meatballs.
Let stand for several minutes.

title: deep fried dolphin(or any white fish)
directions: Take Carnation evaporated milk, pour it into a bowl.
Season milk with garlic salt, onion salt, paprika and parsley flakes. Take dolphin, snapper, grouper (or any other white fish); marinate in milk sauce for 15 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Cut fish into bite-size pieces before marinating.
While fish is soaking, season flour with same ingredients and same amounts as you did the milk sauce (garlic salt, onion salt, paprika and parsley flakes).
Add pepper to flour; mix in a large baggie.
Heat oil to medium-high heat until real hot.
Remove cut-up pieces of fish from milk sauce, dip in flour mixture and coat well.
Then fry in oil until brown.

title: enchilada casserole(beef and plenty of cheese)
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Add seasoning packages, corn, pinto beans, olives and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: crab fondue
directions: Melt cheeses for about 2 to 3 minutes in microwave, stirring often (or melt in double boiler).
Add other ingredients to cheese and mix thoroughly.
Serve with day-old French bread for dipping. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold a peak. Add cream of tartar, sugar and almond flavoring. Beat until sugar dissolves, then add nuts and crushed crackers. Bake in greased pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°. Let pie cool completely and top with Cool Whip. (Best when allowed to set overnight or for a few hours.)

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all together well and bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes. Take out of oven just before they look done.

title: layered salad
directions: Break up lettuce and layer in bowl (I usually use the better part of two heads if they aren't too large).
Break up half a head of cauliflower or so and layer over lettuce.
Layer 1 medium size onion (chopped) or less according to taste.
Layer 1 pound bacon (cooked and crumbled).
Mix the mayonnaise with the sugar and spread over top (do not mix).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Toss well.

title: sausage chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, bring the water to boiling.
Add frozen vegetables and Italian seasoning to saucepan. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Cut Brown 'N Serve sausages into bite size.

In mixing bowl, stir together the skim milk and cornstarch. Stir milk mixture and sausages into vegetable mixture in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickens and bubbly. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Tear cheese into pieces.
Stir it into the chowder until melted.
Season chowder to taste with salt and pepper. Makes 3 servings.

title: spinach-apple toss
directions: Wash spinach; remove stems and tear the leaves into bite size pieces.
Dry with paper towels and chill.
Just before serving, quarter and slice unpared but washed apples with cores removed. Slice into large chilled salad bowl.
Add spinach and bacon and toss.
Mix well the mayonnaise and orange juice concentrate. Serve dressing separately to spoon over salad.

title: cheryl's chocolate chip delights
directions: Mix Crisco, oleo and white and brown sugars together.
Add eggs, baking soda and salt.
Add flour, mixing thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecans.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake on an air filled cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cake in a punch bowl
directions: Cut or break cake into bite-sized pieces and place in the bottom of punch bowl (or any large bowl).
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Layer over cake.
Layer remaining ingredients in following order:
bananas, pineapple, strawberries and whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts and cherries and/or more strawberries.

title: vermicelli with ricotta sauce
directions: Cook garlic in olive oil and butter for 1 minute.
Add milk, salt, red pepper and pepper.
Bring to an almost boil.
Remove from heat and add Ricotta cheese and Parmesan.
Whisk until smooth; heat through.
Cook vermicelli; put vermicelli and sauce in heated bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan and 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a very large bowl, cream the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and corn flakes. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: lentil soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place beans in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Saute carrots, onions and celery in butter in a large Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Drain beans; add to vegetable mixture.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook an additional 20 minutes.
Add water for a thinner consistency, if desired.
Remove bay leaf.
Yield:
3 quarts. Works great in crock-pot, too.

title: kamaboko shrimp tempura
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Add rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and fry until light brown.

title: johnny mazette
directions: Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cook noodles, then add to the sauce.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Combine all ingredients, except squash.
Place mixture loosely in squash halves.
Bake stuffed squash in pan covered with foil. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until squash is tender.

title: zoo sandwiches
directions: Take a slice of your favorite bread and using cookie cutter cut out the animal shape. Cut 3 shapes the same for each sandwich. Spread filling of your choice on one sandwich slice. Place another slice on top. Spread on more filling. Put third slice on.
Now sandwich will stand up on plate.

title: cold pizza
directions: Cover pizza pan with softened cream cheese; cover with a layer of pizza or taco sauce.
Sprinkle with any or all remaining ingredients you wish using the chips to scoop up onto and eat. This makes a great snack.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and wash chestnuts; dice into small pieces.
Mix together all ingredients, adding spinach a little at a time.

title: e-z rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine ingredients and put batter into greased or sprayed muffin cups. Bake in oven until golden brown, about 20 to 30 minutes. This recipe makes 6 big muffins or 12 small ones.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Dredge chops in flour.
Place in baking dish and cover with other ingredients.
Bake chops in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and seasonings.
Sprinkle cheese over top and arrange sliced eggs on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour or until bubbly.
Remove lid and lightly brown.

title: deviled cauliflower
directions: Put salt in boiling water.
Add cauliflower.
Cook until tender (15 to 20 minutes), turning to cook uniformly.
Remove to serving dish.
Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Mix.
Pour over cooked cauliflower.

title: crispy biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like corn meal.
Add all milk and mix to smooth dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: walking taco
directions: Spread dip on platter.
Mix together the avocados, sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of the dip.
Add the rest of the layers in order given. Eat with chips.

title: bean dip
directions: In a pan, mix together refried beans, cheese, onion and hot sauce.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring until heated. Keep warm over a candle warmer. Serve with tortilla chips to dip. Makes 3 cups.

title: creamy chicken pot pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat first 3 ingredients in 4 cups of water and a teaspoon of butter.
Season to desired taste.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 35 minutes or until nearly done.
When chicken is done, reserve 1/4 cup broth.
Cool chicken slightly, remove skin; cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: monterey rice(hot)
directions: Cook rice until tender and mix well with sour cream.
Spread one inch layer of rice mixture in a 6 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange a thin layer of peppers on top of rice and top with thin slices of cheese.
Repeat layers.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut equal amounts of broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Slice onion into very thin slices. Mix equal amounts of sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice and garlic salt.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate for 6 hours before serving.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Shrimp are optional or may be substituted with chicken.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add whole cloves of garlic, sliced onion and chuck beef.
Keep stirring until meat is brown and broken up.
Add paste and warm water (measured in same cans) and stir slowly until sauce is smooth.
Add at least 15 shakes of basil leaves, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Cover and simmer gently 1 hour.
Keep checking sauce to be sure it is simmering gently.
If needed, add more water and basil leaves.
Cook linguini or spaghetti in large pot of boiling water until tender.
Drain. Serve covered with meat sauce.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine celery and onion with oleo.
Cook until tender.
Cook potatoes and drain.
Blend 1 cup of milk with flour and combine with potatoes. Add remaining milk and other ingredients. Then simmer.

title: gran-gran's hot cheese dreams
directions: Mix well and spread on sandwich bread. Brush both sides of sandwich with melted butter and bake in hot oven until brown. Serve immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until well mixed.
Add both kinds of syrup and beat well.
Add vanilla, butter and 1 cup of pecans. Mix well.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Use raw pie crust.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In a bowl, blend together soup, milk, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir in cheese, tuna and pimiento.
Gently fold in cooked macaroni.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle atop casserole.
Sprinkle paprika over top of bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curried papaya kapalua
directions: In a bowl, combine cheeses, chutney and curry powder and blend the mixture until it is smooth.
Add water chestnuts and raisins and combine the mixture well.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Halve lengthwise and seed papayas.
Divide the cheese mixture among the halves, sprinkle halves with the cinnamon-sugar and drizzle them with butter.
Arrange the halves on a lightly buttered baking sheet and bake them in a preheated very hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes or until the tops are golden and transfer them to a heated serving dish.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip into egg, then crumbs. Saute in oil until golden brown.
Place layer of eggplant in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, oregano and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with some of the sauce.
Repeat until all eggplant is used.
Top last layer of sauce with several slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until sauce is bubbly and cheese melted.
Very good.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Remove any skin from chicken.
Cut each breast half in 5 or 6 pieces. Combine yogurt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in chicken pieces and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. (This can be done the night before.)
Roll chicken pieces in dry bread crumbs. Add sesame seed for flavor and crunch.
Put on foil covered pan. Drizzle lightly with melted margarine. Bake about 40 minutes and turn. Bake another 20 minutes or until pieces are tender.
Cooking time:
approximately 1 hour.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in tightly covered container.
To prepare:
Add 1/4 cup mix to 3/4 cup hot water and stir.
Excellent gift idea.
Store in quilted jelly jars, tie with a ribbon and tape a card with instructions on the side.

title: english toffee dessert
directions: Place half crumbs in bottom of pan.
Place all above mixed ingredients in pan.
Add rest of crumbs on top.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Very rich!

title: baked lasagna
directions: Add 1/2 cup water to spaghetti sauce.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, cover bottom of pan with spaghetti sauce.
Layer noodles, then add cheeses, then layer sauce, noodles and cheeses, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marty's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and spread over meat.

title: broccoli moutarde
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on label; drain.
Stir in mustard and sprinkle with dill seed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Spread cream cheese in 8 to 9-inch pie plate.
Top with chili (or beans), olives and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with chips (Fritos) or tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Form into golf ball size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets, 2-inches apart. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Don't overbake. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Put 1/2 of mixture in jello ring mold.
Chill until firm (at least 1 1/2 hours).
Leave remaining mix at room temperature.
Spread sour cream on chilled half; cover with remaining jello mix.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain turkey and onion.
Mix together next 8 ingredients and add to cooked meat.
In large bowl, mix together next 4 ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred beef.
Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Shape into ball.
Can roll in nuts.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Mix with spoon.
Pinch off 1 teaspoon (very small).
Drop in boiling chicken broth and cook for 5 minutes.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat and season to taste.
Add Ro-Tel and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Layer this in pan over Doritos.

title: gingersnap spread
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, red pepper jelly and salt. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add crushed pineapple and fold together.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Spread cooked broccoli in greased 7 x 12-inch pan.
Cover broccoli with cooked chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread on top of chicken.
Butter, bread crumbs and cheese top layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with fork and spread with the fingers in 9-inch pie plate.
Don't roll! Makes 1 crust.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add picante sauce and cheese.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: marinated horn button mushrooms
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms in olive oil.
Cover with French dressing; add garlic.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Makes 4 servings.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Fill muffin pan about half full.
Bake in 400° oven until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in ice water sufficient to cover with 1/2 cup salt for 3 hours.
Scald 1 quart vinegar, sugar, celery seed, dill and pickling spice.
Put in cucumbers and onions.
Just heat through.
Put in hot jars and seal (process). Simmer in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In one mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs, 1/3 cup oil and 1 cake mix.
In second bowl, beat 2 eggs, 1/3 cup oil and other cake mix.
To the chocolate mix, add chocolate chips and to the white mix, add coconut.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of chocolate mix on greased cookie sheet.
On top of chocolate, add 1/2 teaspoon of the white coconut mix.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: bailey irish cream
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Refrigerate and mix well before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Spoon half the crumbs into a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Top with chicken.

title: vegetable quesadillas
directions: Combine sweet pepper, leek, jalapeno, garlic, oil, chili powder, cumin and salt in microwave-safe 1-quart dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: layer salad(use a large glass vertical bowl.)
directions: Put shredded lettuce in bottom of a large, vertical bowl.
Add onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper (don't forget).
Add green peppers and mushrooms. Again, sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper.
Spread unthawed peas over all.
Cover entirely with mayonnaise, sealing to sides of bowl 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top. Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: yellow rice with chicken
directions: Use chicken broth to cook rice; if more liquid is needed, use water.
Add cooked chicken; cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix the cream cheese and butter.
Add the powdered sugar, pudding, milk and Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Place Oreos in a plastic Ziploc bag and crush.
Layer pudding and cookie crumbs in a plastic flowerpot, leaving crumbs on top.
Decorate with an artificial flower and a shovel for serving.
Add gummy worms to dirt, if desired.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Combine soup, paprika and pepper. Set aside.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, overlap potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese. Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with margarine.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage, drain well and crumble over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well, pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 8.

title: carrot bread
