directions: Put into machine in order listed and bake on quick bread cycle. It may seem like this isn't enough liquid; but it really is. Enjoy!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oatmeal and soda.
Stir and let set until cool.
Cream together Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
After this is creamed, add oatmeal mixture.
Then add flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Last of all, stir in chopped nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake.

title: wiener bean pot
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, then make loaves and wrap in aluminum foil.
Put shiny side of foil to the meat. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Next day, poke hole in bottom of foil with toothpick.
Place in rack or broiler pan over 1/2 inch of water.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Let cool before refrigerating.

title: corn fritters
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Mix yolks with corn, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour like pancakes onto hot greased griddle.
Brown 2 minutes and turn. Serve topped with butter.

title: fish creole
directions: Spread butter on baking pan.
Dice vegetables and place in pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place fish on vegetables and pour tomato sauce over entire pan.
Dot with more butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until fish is brown.

title: butter butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light.
Beat in egg and extract.
Gradually blend in flour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Dissolve soda in sour milk, add to creamed mixture.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to batter and mix well.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased pan.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients and moisten with stock.
Will make enough to stuff a 10 pound turkey or a large bread pan.
Heat oven to 425° and bake until good and brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt together and add to mixture a little at a time until blended well together.
Add flavoring. Place into a well-greased and floured cake or tube pan.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool and remove from pan.
Wrap well in foil or place in a tightly fitted cake container.

title: halloween creepy jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into jellos.
Mix 3 minutes or until dissolved. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until very firm.
Dip bottom of pan in hot water 15 seconds.
Cut into Halloween shapes with cookie cutters.
Lift from pan and place on chilled platter. Garnish with your own ideas.
Your little goblins will gobble them up.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ingredients in layers as listed above.
Mix soup with milk and pour over top. Add remaining noodles.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine sugar and spices in a bowl.
Add beans, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 375° or until top cracks.

title: basic muffins("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Separate eggs.
Set whites aside.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add milk to egg yolks and beat.
Add this to flour mixture and beat until perfectly smooth.
Add melted butter to mixture and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour on heated waffle iron.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter until soft. Add meat and seasonings and brown lightly.
Cook macaroni as directions call for.
Mix macaroni, beef and cheese together and pour into baking dish with tomatoes.
Put cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes at moderate heat.

title: meat pone
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet, stirring constantly.
Drain off fat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add green pepper and pimento. Spread in two 16 x 10 x 2-inch baking pans.
Pour corn bread batter over meat mixture.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve meat side up with tomato sauce, mushroom sauce or gravy.
Yields approximately 12 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and water; mix with remaining ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out.
Flour and cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Stir in milk, melted butter and raisins; stir just enough to mix.
Put 6 or 8 spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet, about 1 or 2-inches apart. Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°, until light brown.

title: mcdonald's big mac sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Place sauce in sealed bowl and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain.
Mix tuna, soup and mushrooms.
Mix with cooked macaroni.
Layer 1/2 of this mixture in baking dish.
Layer partially cooked broccoli (steam for 3 to 4 minutes).
Cover with remaining macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello delight
directions: Use Jell-O dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
(You may add walnut pieces.)
For a different flavor, change to orange Jell-O and a can of mandarin oranges.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/8-inch slices (with or without peel). Cut carrots up into small pieces and cut up onions.
Salt and pepper as desired and cut up butter into pats.
Arrange on top of vegetables in a covered casserole.
Microwave on HIGH for 5 minutes.
Stir and turn casserole.
Continue to bake at 5 minute intervals, turning each time.
Takes approximately 15-20 minutes. Very good.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well and arrange in casserole.
Mix curry powder, sugar and butter.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(I use large cans of fruit.
Also, it is better to heat the butter, sugar and curry mixture so as to spread it easier.)

title: fried crab with black bean sauce
directions: Heat frying pan.
Fry crab, ginger and garlic with peanut oil. Mash black beans. Add salt, m.s.g., shoyu, sake and water. Add the seasoned mixture to the fried crab.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
When crab is cooked, add cornstarch mixed with water. Cook only until gravy is thickened. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: ruby pears
directions: Mix together above ingredients except pears and cook on medium heat, stirring until clear and thickened.
Drain pears, place in baking dish and put cherry in middle.
Spread mixture over pears.
Bake at 350° 15-20 minutes.

title: hot dog and hot peppers(canned)
directions: Bring vinegar, water, Wesson oil, salt and sugar to a boil. Cut hot dogs and peppers; pack into jars, approximately 8 to 10 pints.
Fill jars with boiled solution.
Seal and process for 15 minutes in hot water bath.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Fold in bananas, nuts and dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed baked pork chops
directions: Cut a pocket in each chop.
Make a dressing of bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons of the butter, onions, seasonings and a small amount of water.
Place the dressing on pocket of each chop.
Place chops in a roasting pan.
Cover with sauce made by combining water and catsup.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, basting frequently.

title: janet sutherland's lasagna primavera
directions: Bring 3 quarts of water to a boil in a 6-quart pan over high heat.
Add lasagna noodles and cook 5 minutes.
Add carrots; cook 2 more minutes.
Add broccoli, zucchini and crookneck squash. Cook the final 2 minutes or until pasta is tender.
(I cooked 30 seconds more.)
Drain well.
Squeeze liquid out of thawed spinach. Combine spinach with Ricotta cheese.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham crackers with 1 stick melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 2 sticks butter and confectioners sugar. Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Cover with drained crushed pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Add cherries and nuts; drizzle Hershey's chocolate syrup over.
Let set at least 4 hours (refrigerator).
If possible, let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cherry upside-down cake
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread undrained pineapple followed by the cherry pie filling.
Mix cake batter per instructions on its box and pour over the pineapple and cherry mixture.
Spread nuts over last.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove and allow to cool in pan.
When cooled, remove by turning upside-down and lifting pan from cake.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: cinnamon custard
directions: In large bowl, combine, milk, eggs, honey and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon evenly on top.

title: cocoa cheesecake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; cool 15 minutes.

title: pear preserves
directions: Mix sliced pears and sugar together.
Let sit in covered bowl overnight on counter.
Do not refrigerate.
Next day, cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours, stirring often.
Sugar will turn syrupy. While hot, put in small jelly jars and put new lids on the jars. Tighten well with jar rings.
Lids will seal overnight.
Do not press center of lid down.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: First cream the cheese with the sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Last of all, fold in cream after whipping it.
Put into refrigerator trays and freeze for 3 to 4 hours.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt sugar and oleo. Add milk and let come to a boil.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat.

title: orange cake dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Break half of cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next four ingredients together.
Set aside.
Pour 1 can mandarin oranges over cake pieces.
Pour 1/2 mixture over oranges.
Add rest of cake pieces, then second can of oranges, then top with rest of mixture.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix fruit juices together and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and food coloring.
Pour over a block of ice in punch bowl.
Serves 50.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, toss together the chopped apple and lemon juice.
Stir in raisins, grapes and celery.

title: peppernuts
directions: Sift flour once before measuring.
Cream shortening; add sugar, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Add some dry ingredients to shortening and sugar mixture.
Mix water and molasses and add alternately with the flour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Brush tops with water and bake.
Frost or roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in walnuts, cocoa or coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix sugar and melted butter.
Combine ingredients.
Place in an airtight container and place in the refrigerator.
Grease muffin tins and spoon in dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onion, margarine and all spices for about 10 minutes or less, then combine two beaten eggs and 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese with zucchini.
Put in 10-inch ungreased dish or pie pan.
Bake at 375° 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Place the oil in a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Heat it to about 350°.
Using a wooden spoon or whisk, quickly stir in 3 cups of flour all at once.
When the flour is thoroughly mixed in, check the consistency; it should form a smooth paste that is neither runny or clumpy nor grainy.
If the roux is too thin, add some more flour.
If it is too thick, add some more oil.
Cook and stir until it reaches desired stage of doneness. Peanut-butter-colored roux (which looks like it sounds) will take 20 to 30 minutes.
A medium roux will take 30 to 45 minutes; it should be a solid medium brown with a hint of gold in it.
A dark roux will take 50 to 70 minutes; it should be dark brown, but not black.
Recipe can be halved or portion not used frozen.

title: lime delight molded salad
directions: For Jell-O:
Use 1 cup of water and 1 cup of pineapple juice. Blend in marshmallows to hot jello.
Combine rest of ingredients together, except mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Now blend in mayonnaise and whipped cream separately.
Last step, refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 (8-inch) pies.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Prepare rice to directions.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in half and half and broth until thick.
Stir in chicken, mushrooms, parsley, almonds and cooked rice.
Bake in casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large pot; drain fat. Add remaining ingredients; stir. Bring to a boil and simmer for at least 30 minutes. Serve with shredded cheddar cheese and nacho chips.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, salt, pineapple juice and margarine in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool.
Fold in marshmallows, fruits, almonds and whipped cream. Let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rolls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water and sugar and let set for 3 minutes. Then add remaining ingredients. Work in flour and more flour, approximately 4 pounds. Let stand approximately 2 hours. Knead and make rolls and let rise again. Bake at 425 degrees until golden brown.

title: apple cheese torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Blend well. Press mixture into the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: potato fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Place mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Pour melted mixture over potato mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Press into an 8-inch square pan and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix ground chuck and onion with 1/2 cup tomato sauce, crushed cracker crumbs, pepper and salt.
Place meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard, brown sugar and water together.
Spread over meat.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: bread and butter sweet pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and let stand for 2 hours.
Rinse with water.
Mix the vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 1 hour (cover the pan).
Bring pickles to a boil for 2 minutes.
Pack in jars and process for 15 minutes.

title: mini cherry cobblers
directions: Set aside some of the pie filling, including 5 cherries for garnish.
Divide the remaining filling among five ungreased 6 ounce ramekins or custard cups.
Top each with a biscuit; brush with butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over biscuits. Bake at 375° for 14 to 18 minutes or until biscuits are browned. Top with reserved pie filling.

title: preacher's pot roast
directions: Flour, season and sear meat in large skillet.
Place in a greased deep dish pan that has a lid.
Cover meat with all the vegetables.
Mix in a large bowl, the 2 cans of soup, the bouillon water, and dry soup mix and pour over meat and vegetables.
Place lid on pan and bake at 350° until meat is fully cooked, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: "pralines"(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, buttermilk, salt and pecan halves in
a 4 quart casserole; stirring well.	Microwave on High for 12 to 13	minutes.
Stir	every 4 minutes.
Stir in soda until foamy. Microwave
on
High
to	1 1/2 minutes.	Beat with a wooden spoon
until
mixture
just begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop
by
tablespoon
onto	greased waxed paper.
Let stand
until firm.
May
dip
with tongs into melted chocolate morsels	if desired.
Return to waxed paper to cool.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: lettuce topping
directions: Chill.
Mix well and pour over leaf lettuce.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Open pork and beans.
Add catsup, brown sugar and small amount of cooking oil or bacon.
Bake in 300° oven until bubbly or cook in skillet on top of stove or "slap" in the microwave.

title: cran relish salad
directions: Grind oranges and cranberries.
Mix in the sugar until dissolved.
Stir in the pineapple.
Let set.
Dissolve jello in water.
Drain relish somewhat and mix relish in with the dissolved jello.
Chill until firm.
Makes a large bowl.
Keeps well.

title: pasta with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Chop sun-dried tomatoes (already prepared in oil when purchased), artichoke hearts, roasted peppers, parsley and garlic. Boil linguini pasta; strain.
Return pasta to original pot cooked in; add vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and all ingredients chopped.
Toss and serve with grated cheese on top.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in double boiler over hot water. Add the roasted peanuts.
Cool.
Add the marshmallows and put in a buttered pan, 9 x 13-inch.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 300° in a Bundt pan.
Punch holes in cake with toothpick.
Thicken 1 cup orange juice with confectioners sugar and pour over cake. Refrigerate overnight.
To take out of Bundt pan the next day, warm in oven for a few minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in bacon drippings.
Combine all other ingredients; cook slowly until flavors are well blended, about 15 minutes. Pour sauce over browned ribs.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed cabbages(golumbki)
directions: With sharp knife, cut deep around stem of cabbage.
Place stem up in large kettle with 2 inches of water.
Cover and bring to boil.
As leaves start to wilt, remove with fork to colander; drain.
Need about 24 leaves.
Chop some remaining cabbage to get 1/2 cup.
Set aside.
(Use rest of cabbage for soups, etc.)

title: pasta pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except margarine. In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine.
Add spaghetti mixture, spreading evenly, to form a tight cake.
Cook over medium-low heat until bottom is golden brown, about 10 minutes. Divide the pancake into 4 sections and turn over, one section at a time. Brown 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna salad(low-calorie, low-fat)
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse thoroughly.
Toss lightly with lite Italian dressing in a mixing bowl.
Add onion.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours to marinade.
Cover tightly.
Add celery and cucumber.
Add dill weed.
Add peas (rinse peas to separate).
Toss with macaroni mixture and return to refrigerator, covered for several
hours. Then add tuna, olives, mayo (if desired).
Italian will do nicely alone.
Serve with tomato wedges on lettuce.

title: zesty noodle soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Add all but the noodles. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer 30 minutes. Add noodles. Cook until noodles are done. Serve with crusty French bread.

title: sausage and mash pie
directions: Slowly fry sausage to remove most of the fat to enable the meat to crumble easily.
Let stand until cold.
To the meat, add raw grated potatoes and onion; mix well.
Put into 8-inch pastry shell and cover with pastry.
Neaten the edges with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
This amount will fill two (8-inch) pies.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Salt chicken breasts and pour enough water over them to cook. When tender, pour off bones and cut meat into large pieces (or skin); place in casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Top with Ritz crackers (crush with hands so the crumbs won't be too fine).
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers. Bake in 350° oven and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
When cool and partially set, add the other ingredients and pour into gelatin mold.
Very different taste!
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cashew nut loaf
directions: Grind cashews, dice onion and saute in margarine; melt Vegex into onion and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add in order given; stir well and fill 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat quickly to 325° to 350° and continue baking for about 1 hour.
I do not like under baked pies. This pumpkin pie should look done, and crust well browned.

title: brown sugar sauce
directions: Mix together in a saucepan over medium heat.
Cook until thickened.
This is a good topping for a plain yellow cake or on top of ice cream.

title: frozen zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini for 12 to 15 minutes, or until clear, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Boil mixture for 6 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Pour into plastic containers.
Cover and freeze.
Or it may be kept in refrigerator in jars.
Delicious!

title: mayor's greek style potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Mix
tomato
sauce and oil. Rub tomato mixture on
potatoes
and
place
potatoes
in pan. Drizzle remaining mixture over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake at 325° for 45
to
minutes
or
until edges begin to brown.
Turn often.
May
need
to add a small amount of water to pan if evaporating quickly.

title: peanut sticks
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Cut into finger strips. Place on baking sheet. Toast strips and trimmings in a 250° oven until very dry and light brown.
Make crumbs of trimmings.
Dilute peanut butter with enough oil in bowl to make thick liquid.
Dip sticks into peanut butter mixture to coat.
Roll in crumbs.
Let stand for 12 to 24 hours or until dried. Will keep indefinitely.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning mix and follow directions.
Cool.
Mix all vegetables and cheese.
Pour meat over top and add dressing.
Chill.
Just before serving, add corn chips.
Adjust the amounts of different ingredients to suit individual preferences.

title: canadian chicken
directions: When chicken has cooled, remove the skin and bones and dice the meat. Skim the chicken broth of fat by using a bulb-type baster.
Combine the diced chicken and Canadian bacon.
Melt the margarine in a nonstick skillet and saute the mushrooms and pepper for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and peppers to the meat.

Blend the flour with the chicken broth and milk in a saucepan. Bring this mixture to a boil, stirring to keep it smooth. Add the meat and vegetables to the saucepan along with the wine, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer the entire mixture for 3 minutes.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the vanilla, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix in flour slowly.
Finally, add the Rice Krispies, fold in, do not use mixer.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet, a heaping teaspoonful at a time.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 48 cookies.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until mixture comes to a rolling boil; cook 1 minute.
Stir to keep from boiling over.
Remove from heat and add a few drops of green food coloring and one 6 ounce bottle liquid pectin.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars, seal and process.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Cover and cook potatoes until tender, 15 - 20 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Add 1 3/4 c. cheese, milk, butter and salt. Cook over low heat until cheese and butter melt.
Fold in beaten eggs. Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: easy cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas. Add bananas right before serving.

title: neighborhood quick fudge cake
directions: In mixer sifted flour and sugar together.
Bring water, cocoa and butter to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar and mix.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and curry into well drained fruit.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken breasts, cool, skin and debone and cube. Melt together the cream cheese, margarine, onion and mushrooms in saucepan over medium heat.
Add chicken and refrigerate until cool enough to handle.
(Margarine will not blend well until cubed chicken is added.)
Separate crescent rolls, slice them in half and press thinner with hands.
Stuff about 1 tablespoon chicken mixture on rolls and wrap, sealing edges together.
Bake in 325° oven about 20 minutes until brown and hot through and through. Serve hot.
I have also used quail in place of the chicken and it was delicious!
These can be prepared larger and used as a main dish, also.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: To Prepare:
Cream oleo and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: banana balls
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the butter, egg and milk together. Add to dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Peel bananas. Cut in 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Dip into batter, spreading batter evenly over bananas. Fry in hot deep fat at 370° for 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel and serve with honey.

title: peanut butter centers(buckeyes)
directions: Knead with hands until smooth. Shape into balls and dip into chocolate.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix together the ingredients and bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients to make dressing. Toss with mixed greens, onions and strawberries.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; add grated raw zucchini.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken breasts cordon bleu
directions: Flatten breast with cleaver, salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 slice cheese and 1/2 slice of ham on 1/2 chicken piece.
Fold other half over and seal with toothpick.
Dip each in flour, then egg and crumbs.
Saute in melted margarine over medium flame until golden brown.
Continue to cook on low flame until done.
6 servings.

title: cake in orange cups
directions: Cut 12 to 18 (12-inch) squares of heavy-duty foil; set aside. Cut 1-inch slice from top of each orange.
Scoop out orange fruit and pulp.
Leave peel intact as a baking cup.

title: noodles a la russe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and garlic in a skillet.
Drain fat and season with salt and pepper.
Mix together melted margarine, sour cream, cheese and pimento.
Add meat and sour cream mixture to noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg nog(one serving)
directions: Blend egg and sugar together.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Serve cold in tall glass.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut out any bad spots of the apples, remove cores, cut into bite size chunks. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Add sliced celery to apples and toss with mayonnaise. Before serving, add walnuts.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sandwiches or serve on lettuce leaf.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half, lengthwise.
Remove yolk to small bowl. Mash well and add salt, salad dressing, pickle relish and mustard. Mix well.
Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook until shiny and thick.

title: flu cure
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well and it's a sure cure for the flu.

title: apricot-jello cake
directions: Mix
well
in
order: cake mix, jello, nectar, eggs and oil; put
in
Bundt pan;
flour and grease pan.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hard tack
directions: Stir until moist.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Take off cookie sheet and brake into crumbs.
Mix with 1 large Cool Whip or 1 quart whipping cream.
Add vanilla.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add peanut butter and honey.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: caramel-coconut squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and mix well. Pat into ungreased 9 x 9 x2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine milk, butterscotch pieces, coconut and vanilla.
Spread over partially baked layer.
Bake at 350° until golden brown around edges, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cookies will not appear set, but will firm up as they cool.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 36.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Over low heat, melt margarine and flour; cook until smooth. Stir in chicken broth, 1 cup milk and soups; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add peas and carrots.
Add chicken.
Warm over low heat.
Server over Pepperidge Farm shells.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine eggs, syrup, butter, vanilla, salt and sugar; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla. Sift flour and baking powder together and add to mixture. Roll very thin on floured board. Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 300° to 350° or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) with milk.
Add mashed bananas; add flour, soda and salt. Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Put into 2 greased and floured large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ruth cheek's rice dressing
directions: Mix well and pour into a large baking dish.
Cover with foil and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apricot roll
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients very well.
Fold in apricots.
Form into a ball or log, then roll in ground nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until cold.
Best served with Triscuit wafers.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mash persimmons through a colander.
Add sour milk.
Add other ingredients in order, blending well.
Bake in a well buttered baking pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: corned beef hash balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of marbles.
Roll in egg and bread crumbs and fry in deep fat about 30 seconds or until browned.
Serve with hot savory cocktail sauce.
Insert a toothpick in each ball.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen balls.

title: fajitas
directions: Mix garlic, cumin, chili powder, crushed red pepper, vegetable oil and lemon juice together.
Marinate chicken or beef in mixture for at least 1 hour.
Cut meat into strips.
Stir-fry meat.
Chop vegetables.
Remove meat.
Stir-fry vegetables with any remaining marinade.
Serve in flour tortilla or over rice.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg together.
Press down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on top of first ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: excellent roasting sauce
directions: This is great on meatballs or roast and then cooked in crock-pot on high 8 to 10 hours. This recipe is for 3 pounds meatballs or roast.

title: light bread pudding
directions: Cover sides and bottom of a deep casserole dish.
Mix all of the other ingredients and pour into dish.
Place slices of light bread on top.
Some of the pecans can be reserved to be placed on top of light bread.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and rinse the artichokes and cut into chunks.
Mix everything and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown 1 pound of sausage and drain.
Saute 1/2 cup each red and green bell pepper and chopped onion.
Mix these together with flour.
Beat eggs well and mix with milk.
Add to sausage and vegetable mixture along with cheese.
Pour in 2 pie shells and bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: Using a mixer, combine milk and pudding mix; stir in melted chocolate squares (will be thick).
Fold in 1 container of Cool Whip with a spoon.
Pour into pie crust.
Over this, spread as much of the second container of Cool Whip as you want.
Sprinkle chocolate sprinkles on top.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in chicken broth.
Add margarine and flour mixture, then add about 1 pint of half and half.
Stir over medium heat until hot and thick.
Add grated sharp cheese and serve.

title: bisquick cobbler
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, Bisquick and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch dish.
Pour in melted butter.
Spoon filling in, distributing evenly in dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If you like more fruit add another 1/2 can of filling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in a storage bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Divide mixture in half and roll in a second cup of pecans.

title: microwave easy fudge
directions: Stir sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk on top of sugar and cocoa.
Cut margarine into small pieces on top of milk.
Cook 2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in pan. Put in freezer 35 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: rhubarb creme pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk; add to sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add cut rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 425° oven until rhubarb is tender and filling is set.
Beat egg whites.
Add the brown sugar. Pour over pie; bake until brown.

title: spinach salad with raspberry dressing
directions: Heat together all of the ingredients (except spinach). Remove from heat and pour over spinach.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: You git a pot out.
Put hot water in it.
Turn on the stove. After a while, about 15 minutes, go back into the kitchen check on the water.
See if it is boiling if it is, put in noodles.
Then put in the cheese and a little milk.
Stir it.
After stirring it let it cool off.
Then off you go to eat.

title: scalloped potatoes(fat controlled, low-cholesterol)
directions: In an oiled casserole, place a layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with flour and place a layer of onions; alternate potatoes, onions and flour until all are used.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat oleo and milk together and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour to brown top.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus into small pieces and steam until tender in a little water. Thicken milk with flour; add salt, pepper and butter. Add grated cheese and cooked asparagus to milk mixture. Arrange in	alternating layers with bread crumbs in an oiled baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted and dish heated through.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco. Add a little sugar at a time until all is in. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each egg. Cream together well. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add milk and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: asparagus venetian
directions: In 8-inch dish, place asparagus (cook a little until tender). Drizzle with onion and butter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes in 325° oven.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square baking dish or pie plate. Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese into dish.
Beat 1 minute or until smooth the remaining ingredients.
Pour into dish and bake 30 to 35 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Stand 5 minutes before cutting.
You can add 1 cup chicken, too.
Bake 50 minutes for Chicken Bake.

title: kyra's mild or hot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set the 12 pieces of chicken on a greased pan.
Shake on the seasoning salt, granulated onion and granulated garlic.
The more you add, the spicier it tastes.
Put it in the oven and bake for one hour or until slightly browned and it doesn't bleed.
Turn off the oven and let cool 5 to 10 minutes. Then serve and enjoy.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
In bowl, mix water, eggs and cake mix.
Stir in drained pineapple and half the coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasteda
directions: Boil elbow macaroni; only half cook, about 8 minutes.
Mix eggs and Ricotta until smooth.
Add other ingredients, including half cooked macaroni.
Mix well.
Grease with oil a 10 x 13-inch pan (preferably glass, Pyrex or Corning Ware).
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven.
Cool and cut into squares and serve.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
May be reheated or eaten cold.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Add tomato sauce (1 can of water to each can of sauce) in pot. Season with salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Cut sausage into 2-inch pieces.
Add to sauce and cook for 1 hour.
Cut peppers and onions into strips.
Add to sauce.
Cook until tender.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter 8-inch square pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar with flour and baking powder in large bowl.
Work in butter with fingers or pastry blender until mix resembles coarse meal. Add eggs and milk and blend.
Spoon into pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture evenly over top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, place potatoes with enough water to cover (in skins).
Cook until fork-tender.
Drain potatoes and set aside until cool enough to handle.
Thinly slice potatoes.
Cool completely.

title: easy rotini and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add mushrooms with liquid, water and bouillon; bring to boil.
Stir in uncooked rotini.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until rotini is tender.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cut up all fresh vegetables and cover with water.
When they are soft after cooking on medium heat, add hamburger and Veg-All. Cook on simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix the
cream	of
chicken
soup and the tuna together with hand
beater.
Add	water
to
empty can; add to mixture. Butter a 9
x 13-inch pan.
Put in noodles; add the mixture to it.
If
not wet
enough, add more water.
Salt and pepper to taste;
butter may
also
be added.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until thick.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Add refried beans in 9 x 13 dish. Add avocado dip on top. Add sour cream mixture on top. Add green onions on top. Add tomatoes on top. Add shredded cheese on top.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cake.

title: crisp pickles(copied from 1939)
directions: Soak cukes overnight in cold water.
Drain; pack in jars with a stick of horseradish in center and a slice of onion on top. Boil sugar, salt and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: world's fastest fish!(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Lightly oil baking pan; set aside.
Cut fish fillets into 4 serving pieces.
Mix milk and salt together. Turn cracker crumbs into a large pie plate.
Dip each piece of fish into milk, then crumbs, then milk, then crumbs again to coat thoroughly.
Place fish pieces in the oiled baking pan.
Liberally sprinkle 1 tablespoon of oil all over tops of fish pieces.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until fish flakes lightly with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: herb butter
directions: Crush bouillon cubes and chop basil and parsley.
Mix well and spread on both sides of slices.
Reassemble loaf and wrap in heavy foil.
Freeze.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° taken directly from freezer.
This makes enough for 3 (9-inch) round loaves.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together; sprinkle each muffin with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon, combined.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May be done in the blender.
Great on ribs or for cooking on the grill.
If you would like it thicker, cut the water in half.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions. Combine 1/2 cup tomato soup and 1 cup cheese.
Cut peppers lengthwise.
Place in baking dish. Stuff with mixture.
Place excess around peppers.
Pour remainder of the soup over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Remove and sprinkle cheese over.
Bake 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix together until smooth. Dip shrimp into batter and fry.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Bake cake in layers or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Follow directions on box for baking.

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Melt chocolate bark.
Spread peanut butter on Ritz crackers. Put them together like sandwiches.
Dip into melted chocolate. Put on wax paper until chocolate hardens.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Grease 1 large baking dish.
Put cherries and pineapple (don't drain) into baking dish.
Stir just a little.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of cherry and pineapple mixture.
Cup up butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, until brown.
Remove from oven.
Add pecans and place in oven 5 minutes.
Let cool for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate drops candy
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze for 15 minutes or longer.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.

title: good luck punch
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces. Add water to cover. Cook until soft, about 10 minutes. Drain through cheesecloth bag or sugar sack. Measure: should be 3 quarts juice. Dissolve sugar in 2 cups water. Cook 10 minutes to make a syrup. Add lemon juice, pineapple and rhubarb juices. Pour over chunk of ice in punch bowl. Just before serving, add ginger ale. Makes 1 gallon (24 servings).

title: salmon chowder
directions: Chop and dice all vegetables.
Cook in olive oil until soft. Coat with flour and brown 2-3 minutes until truly browned.
Add 5 cups of liquid all at once.
Stir until boiling and thickened. Reduce heat, add smoked salmon (cut into small pieces), oregano or dill and salt and pepper.
Cook until well heated.
Add raw salmon for the last 5 minutes of cooking.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Garnish with parsley.

title: date log
directions: Melt butter, add sugar.
Stir until melted.
Add dates and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and cereal.
Mix well; cool.
Roll in shape of log, then roll in powdered sugar. Cool well before slicing.

title: turkey wings supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate wings at joints.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in salad oil, fry a few pieces at a time, until browned.
Put wings in roasting pan.
Combine soup, salt, pepper and paprika (do not dilute); spread over wings.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: syrup candy
directions: Put sugar, sorghum and water in a saucepan.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook until threads form and break off when tested with a spoon.
Now, add the butter and soda.
Stir and pour into a buttered bowl.
When it is cool enough to handle, grease hands and pick it up and pull it several times.
It will turn a golden color.
Two people pulling the same lump can make it fun.
Put on plates and let it cool.

title: honey gingered chicken
directions: Combine honey, chilli sauce or catsup, soy sauce and ginger and pour over chicken.
Let marinate for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: pepsi-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
Melt butter; add cocoa and Pepsi.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir until well blended.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and frost while still warm.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa and boil 1 minute.
Then add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 90 minute soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, butter and 2 cups of flour. Beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in additional flour to make stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place, free from draft for 40 minutes.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board. Divide in half.
Divide each half into 6 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into a 20-inch long rope.
Shape each rope into a pretzel. Place on greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rest 5 minutes. Combine egg yolk and 1 tablespoon of water.
Brush each pretzel with egg yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, onion, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Slice rolls in half.
Layer with mix on top and bottom, then layer on bottom with ham, topped with cheese.
Replace top of bread and place in aluminum pans that rolls came in.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead of time, refrigerated then baked just before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar into a crumb mixture. Put 2/3 of crumbs in baked pie shell.
Cook in double boiler, scald milk.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Put into milk, stir in 3 egg yolks beaten, cook until thick.
Stir in 2 Tbsp. peanut butter 1/4 tsp. vanilla, let cool. Pour in pie shell over powdered sugar and peanut butter crumbs.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef until done, stirring to crumble.

Drain. Stir flour into butter in a Dutch oven; cook over low heat 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly until a smooth paste is formed. Gradually stir in water; cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly. Stir in cooked ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Bring soup to a boil; cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dick van holland's favorite chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients very lightly, reserving grapes for topping.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shredded potato and ham pie
directions: Combine eggs, ham, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, peas, mushrooms, ham, milk and onion. Set this aside.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup cheese and potatoes to use as pie crust.
Press this onto bottom and up sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Pour filling into potato crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: ron's (soon to be famous) broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together except onions.
Crumble in 1/2 can fried onions.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, crumble other 1/2 can fried onions on top.
Cover and continue baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown celery, onion, garlic and meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and let stew for 45 minutes.

title: chips of chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Combine and blend the first 4 ingredients.
Save 1 cup to sprinkle over top with the 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain.
Layer broccoli and chicken in casserole. Cover with mushrooms.
Make sauce with soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and broth.
Pour sauce over mushrooms. Cover with American cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and mix well. Place in a buttered casserole, then sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: vanilla cake
directions: Put eggs, vinegar, flour and milk together.
Stir it, then put into oven for 5 seconds.
Take out and put icing on, then eat.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight.

title: spinach salad delight
directions: Top spinach leaves with cottage cheese and remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 serving.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in tight lidded jar or container.
Mix very well.
Marinate at least overnight in refrigerator.

title: fig preserves
directions: Fill Dutch oven or a large pan with figs that have had stems trimmed.
Cover completely with sugar (no figs showing).
Cover with a clean cloth and let set overnight outside the refrigerator.

title: frosted molasses creams
directions: Cream butter, sugar and molasses.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and flour sifted with soda and salt.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter. Bake at 375° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not grease cookie sheet. Makes a lot of cookies.
Frost with 1 recipe Seven Minute Icing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together until smooth.
Add Dream Whip.
Drain the pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges.
Slice bananas (medium thickness).
Add fruit, marshmallows and 1 cup nuts to Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Fold in with wooden spoon.
Top with remaining nuts.
Chill.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Rinse sauerkraut in cold water really good.
Squeeze out water.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar; pour out.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate all day or overnight.

title: "winter" strone soup
directions: Bring water to a boil, add beans and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and soak 1 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Cook beef and onion in hot frying pan until beef is warmed.
Stir beef mixture into beans.
Bring bean mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and boil gently until beans are tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Break up large pieces of tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients, except macaroni, to bean mixture.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of 3-quart oblong casserole.
Use enough bread to cover the bottom.
Brown and drain sausage.
Mix sausage and mustard.
Spread over bread.
Cover with cheese slices.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Cook from room temperature in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed like a souffle and set. Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot patch sandwiches
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and grape jelly.
Stir in the cottage cheese, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Put together sandwiches.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place baking dish in a shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Serve plain or with sauce.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butter; add cream and sugar.
Boil 6 minutes.
Turn off heat; leave on stove.
Stir in marshmallows to melt.
Add crumbs and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: meat loaf (my mom's)
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk (I add a little catsup). Add salt, pepper, baking powder, meat and cracker crumbs. Shape into a loaf. Put in buttered pan with 1 to 4 cups water. Bake at 350° until done. Pour catsup over top of loaf while baking.

title: cowboy sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour into bowl.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg; mix until smooth.
Stir in pie filling, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: betty shaw's sour cream potato salad
directions: Crumble bacon; set some aside for garnish.
In skillet combine soup and sour cream.
Add potatoes, bacon and onions.
Heat just until good and hot.
Garnish with reserved bacon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: best brownies in the world
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: microwave teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Mix teriyaki sauce and catsup; add wings and chill for 3 to 4 hours.
After chilled, pour off marinade and combine with water and cornstarch.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes; stir until boiling.
On a glass plate, arrange wings, spoke fashion, and baste with sauce.
Microwave, covered, for 4 to 5 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn and baste.
Cook for another 4 to 5 minutes.
Broil if desired.
May be baked in conventional oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: clarice's pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for beets. Bring to a boil and boil for 15-20 minutes. Add beets and bring to a full boil again for 10 minutes. Put into sterilized jars immediately and seal with sterilized tops. Makes 7-8 quarts.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring sugar, Karo syrup and margarine or butter to boil. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour over Special K cereal in a 9 x 13-inch pan (pat down).

title: mexi beef and bean dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in salsa and beans.
Mix well and cook for 5 minutes.
Spread onto bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Arrange tomato over cheese; sprinkle with olives and green onions. Top with sour cream, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: In skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef until the meat is brown and the vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Take brown sugar and margarine; put in skillet and cook until chocolate brown, then add 1/2 cup water.
Cook until this is all dissolved.

title: lime french dressing
directions: In small jar, with tight-fitting lid, combine ingredients; shake well.
Chill to blend flavors.

title: baked apricot casserole
directions: Pour apricots and juice in baking dish, cut side down.
Top with brown sugar and cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have ungreased Bundt pan ready.
Put cut up biscuits in large bowl.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute green onions and vegetables.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle and toss with bacon and cheese.
Spread evenly around Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with cream gravy or honey.

title: vegetable lasagna(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini in microwave-safe dish.
Cover, but leave one corner to vent.
Cook 5 minutes on High or until tender-crisp. Stir in mushrooms. Cover and cook 5 minutes longer. Drain off liquid; set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, blending into mixture. Fold topping over mixture. Pour into prepared crusts. Freeze until firm and serve. Use a 9-inch baked pie shell, if desired.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: chocolate peanutty krispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan; add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat and add cereal and half of peanut butter chips.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Pour the rest of peanut butter chips on top and press them down so they stay put.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all and add chips last.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl. Add milk and egg. Beat until smooth.
Remove skin and bones from salmon and flake with a fork. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Fold into batter.
Fry in hot grease by dropping from a tablespoon.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Pour boiling water over date and soda.
Cool.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
When date mixture is cool, add margarine mixture, flour, baking powder and nuts.
Mix well and bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll in chili powder and paprika.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: favorite fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice.
Mix with lemon juice.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over liquid and stir until well mixed (it begins to thicken).
Add the pineapple and other fruit and stir well.
Must be refrigerated for a while.
Stir before serving.
Can easily double or triple depending on number of servings you want and amount of fruit you are using.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion in skillet, seasoning to taste.
Add beaten egg and rice.
In roasting pan, put a layer of cabbage using half of the cabbage.
Put layer of meat and onion using all of this.
Put layer of cabbage using rest of cabbage.
Pour tomato juice over top of cabbage.
Bake at 350° until cabbage is done, about 2 hours.

title: mock strawberry preserves
directions: Cook figs, sugar and lemon juice 15 minutes, then add Jell-O. Stir and cook 20 minutes.
Pack into hot sterile jars and seal.

title: scampi guadalajara
directions: Beat together butter, onions, garlic, A.1. sauce, lemon, salt and pepper.
Melt over low heat; stir and keep warm.
Do not let brown.
Split shrimp lengthwise, be careful not to cut clear through, and spread open.
Place shrimp, split sides up, in oiled baking dish and broil 4 inches from high flame for 5 minutes. Pour hot butter sauce over shrimp and serve at once.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix together the flour, nuts and margarine and spread in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot (yes, the entire contents of the stuffing box!).
Cook on low for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve on buns.
Enough for a crowd!

title: gourmet vegetable chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in butter over low heat, stirring occasionally until onions are soft. Add flour and blend over low heat for 1 minute.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and half and half, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Simmer 2 minutes, then add grated Cheddar, blending until cheese is melted.
Add ham, Worcestershire sauce, broccoli and other vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat over moderately low heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: bran muffins that keep 6 weeks
directions: Mix the All Bran cereal, white raisins and boiling water together; set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Refrigerate 24 hours before baking.
Batter keeps in the refrigerator 6 weeks.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: grandma's orange pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add fruit juices and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add slowly to egg yolks.
Return to oven and cook 2 minutes more.
Add butter and orange rind. Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven at 350°.
Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in another bowl.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and mix until blended.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins. Mixture will be very stiff.
Spread evenly in pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until top is golden and pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle the bacon in the slightly baked pie crust, then add the spinach, mushrooms, onions and both cheeses.
Mix the half and half, cream cheese, salt, pepper, red pepper, eggs and flour.
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils; drain and place in soup kettle.
Add 8 cups of water and remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes; simmer, covered, 30 minutes more. Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: In 4-quart heavy pot, saute sausage.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add oil to drippings and saute green pepper, garlic and celery for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with liquid, broth and onions. Stir in spices.
Add rice, which has been washed.
Add sausage and cook 30 minutes, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally.
After most liquid has been absorbed by rice, add shrimp and cook until pink.
Transfer to an oblong baking dish and bake for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: vickie's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Put in large pot.
Add seasoning as directed on package.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato juice and sauce.
Add chopped tomatoes and chili hot beans.
Heat until hot. Enjoy.
Eat up.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and sugar in a bowl and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
In bowl, combine condensed milk and coconut.
Spread over crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool in pan; cut into 2-inch bars.
If desired, melt 6 ounces of chocolate chips and spread over top of bars.

title: tuna ring
directions: Prepare tuna, onions and celery; mix together in a large bowl. Over low heat, warm tomato soup and cream cheese until cheese melts.
(Can use a mixer to help blend.)
Remove from heat.
Mix gelatin and water; add to soup mixture and stir well.
Add mayonnaise to soup mixture; stir well.
Pour into bowl with tuna, onions and celery, mixing well.
Pour into mold which has been sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: italian sausage sauce
directions: Cut sausage in 2 inch pieces, fry in skillet.
In large pot put oil, pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients with 16 oz. water.
Simmer. Salt to taste.

title: mocha au lait mix
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk powder, instant coffee, brown sugar and mini chocolate chips. Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour and margarine and press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: In a large bowl, separate raw hamburger into very fine pieces. Mix with taco seasoning and onion.
Microwave for 6 minutes; stir about halfway through cooking time.
In same bowl, add remaining ingredients.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease muffin pan and fill cups about half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes about 32 rolls.

title: macaroni fish salad
directions: In bowl, combine macaroni, fish, onion, salt, pepper and green pepper.
Toss lightly.
Add water and dry mustard; mix well.
Add mayonnaise and toss.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 2 servings.

title: no fat eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Chill at least 4 hours. Serve with a sprinkle of nutmeg. Serves 3.

title: christmas recipe
directions: Take Jesus as the primary ingredient of Christmas.
Stir in the details of His Birth.
Add a Personal Experience of Faith and Trust.
Spice with the Traditions of the Season.
Add a Sacrificial Gift to Christ.
Top with Fresh Commitment to do God's Will.
Serve with joy to all the world.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg and mix well.
Add the flour and cream.
Dust a board with flour.
Roll the dough very thin.
Cut cookies with a round cookie cutter.
Place on a buttered or nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for about 5 minutes.

title: green beans and potato casserole for 6
directions: Combine green beans, potatoes and celery in 1-quart casserole. Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Saute onion in bacon drippings. Stir in flour.
Add evaporated milk slowly; stir constantly.
Cook until thickened and smooth; stir constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over vegetables in casserole; mix well. Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese, cracker crumbs and crumbled bacon over top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk and cooked pumpkin.
Salt to taste.
Add seasonings: nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Add melted butter.
Bake in cooker 1 hour.

title: crispy pumpkin seeds
directions: Go to a pumpkin patch and pick out a good fresh pumpkin.
Do not pick a rotten one!
Cut off the top with the stem.
Scoop out all the inside stuff and put it into a big bowl.
Pick out all the seeds and rinse them off.
Boil the seeds for 15 minutes in salt water.
Strain.
Spread the seeds onto a salted cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn the seeds and bake until crispy (10 to 20 minutes).
Make a Happy Jack-O-Lantern out of the pumpkin and enjoy eating the crunchy, delicious seeds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but the Parmesan cheese.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook green and white tortelline as directed on package and drain.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend with mixer.
Add other ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: orange strawberry romanoff
directions: Reserve 4 large strawberries and slice remainder into a bowl. Add orange peel and Grand Marnier.
Gently mix; let stand 15 minutes.
In a bowl, whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in sour cream.
Sift powdered sugar over whipping cream and fold in. Place 1 tablespoon of strawberries into each of 4 dessert dishes. Gently fold strawberries into whipped cream mixture.
Spoon mixture over strawberries in dessert dishes and chill until ready to serve.
Decorate with reserved strawberries, cut in fan shape. Serve with cookies.
Serves 4.
Bon appetit.

title: company spanish rice
directions: Heat oil; add garlic and celery.
Brown.
Mix rice, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, bay leaf and pepper with hot water.
Add to celery and garlic.
Stir well and cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Brown beef and green pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chili powder, sugar and beef bouillon. Combine rice and meat mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add water or tomato juice, if necessary.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: egg and chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 1 cup potato chips in a 1-quart greased casserole dish; add eggs.
Blend soup, milk and onion. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over eggs; sprinkle with remaining potato chips.
Bake for 25 minutes, until bubbly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: deer soup(or venison burgoo)
directions: Flour venison chunks and brown in oil in large stew pot.
Add all other ingredients using tomato juice and water to desired thickness of soup.
Cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer all day.
Also great done in crockpot.
Great when served with cornbread and cherry salad.
Serves as many as you want!
I make a stock pot full and freeze what is left.

title: linda's rolls
directions: Put all in a bowl; add flour last as it may not take 8 cups. Stir well; put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll out and dip in butter.
Let rise until ready to bake, about 1 hour.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients. Blend with egg mixture and add nuts.

title: party spinach dip
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cottage cheese. Process until smooth scraping sides of processor bowl once.
Place in a medium bowl and set aside.

title: zippy chicken spread
directions: Blend all ingredients; chill.
Thin to desired consistency with milk.
Spread on crackers.
Garnish with crisp bacon if desired.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, orange rind and orange juice.
Fold in Bran Flakes, pears and pecans.

title: no fail cream puffs
directions: Slice off tops of Anginetti cookies.
Mix whipped cream and cream cheese for 1 minute.
Add pineapple to mixture and blend for another minute.
Drop filling onto cookies by tablespoon; replace tops on cookies.
Refrigerate until served; refrigerate any leftovers.

title: brown rice
directions: Add soup and rice to melted butter.
Stir.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in vegetables.
Drain as much liquid as possible off cucumber and onion.
Add mayonnaise for easier spreading, but don't add too much.
Can be refrigerated overnight to let flavors mingle.
Stir good and spread on bread. Put on top slice, trim edges and cut in desired shapes.
Tastes great on wheat bread.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: In a large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix together.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine last 4 ingredients.
Stir at all times.
Cook over low heat until it comes to a rolling boil.
Cook 1 minute and remove from heat.
Pour over ingredients in bowl. Stir together, then drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let set until they become a little hard.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until slightly brown.

title: freezer alfredo sauce
directions: Mix cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and margarine, heating slowly, stirring frequently until smooth. Add milk to thin until desired consistency for your pasta. Serve over pasta.

title: reese's bars candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and margarine and spread on top.
Refrigerate.
Cut like fudge to serve.

title: crab fondue
directions: Combine cheeses in top of double boiler.
Cook, stirring, until blended together.
Drain crab; flake and add to cheeses. Add cream, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and bubbly.
Place in fondue pot.
Keep hot.
Dip cubed French bread into crab mixture.
Makes 2 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Unthaw spinach and squeeze out excess water.
Place in medium bowl; stir in beaten eggs, then stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(You must mix this the night before you want to bake them.)

title: impossible brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Spread broccoli in plate. Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, baking mix, butter and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed quail
directions: Clean quail by splitting along backbone so you leave the breast and legs whole.
Stuff with your favorite dressing, chicken or turkey.
Wrap a bacon strip around bird.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: speckled coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans.

Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth. Spoon into prepared pans and bake for 25 to 28 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Remove from pans immediately and cool on rack.

title: cafe mexicano(demitasse cups)
directions: In small cups, place 1 teaspoon of chocolate syrup.
Whip cream, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Stir remaining cinnamon into strongly brewed coffee.
Pour coffee into cups.
Top with flavored whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Mix ingredients into cheese mixture.
Add chopped, dried beef.
Chill in ball shape wrapped in Saran.
When chilled well, roll in snipped parsley and garnish with a maraschino cherry.

title: dolly's fruit cake (no bake)
directions: Melt butter with marshmallows.
Pour over mixture.
Mix well and shape into loaf.
Refrigerate.

title: nacho corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, stir both soups and corn.
Gradually stir in milk and water.
Add turkey.
Over medium heat, heat to simmering, stirring occasionally.
Cook 10 minutes.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Makes 6 cups or 6 servings.

title: italian dressing recipe
directions: Shake ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Shake before serving.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Split cake horizontally into 4 equal layers and place bottom cake layer on a serving plate.
Set aside.
Slice ice cream into thirds according to flavors.

Spread top of bottom cake layer with chocolate ice cream; top with a layer of cake; spread with vanilla ice cream; layer of cake; spread with strawberry ice cream and finish with the last layer of cake.
Cover and freeze 1 hour.
Prepare both envelopes of whipped topping, spread over frozen cake top and sides.
Return to freezer until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: ratatouille
directions: In a heavy kettle, heat the oil over moderately high heat until it is hot, but not smoking and in it, saute the eggplant, stirring, until it is golden.
Reduce the heat to moderately low.
Add the onions and the bell peppers and cook the mixture, stirring, until the onions are softened.
Stir in the tomatoes, the garlic, the basil, the oregano, the thyme and salt and pepper to taste and cook the mixture over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Ratatouille may be served hot or at room temperature over your favorite pasta.

title: salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and salsa or tomatoes and green chillies in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or broiled green, red or yellow pepper wedges.
Makes 3 cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Make in a glass bowl.
Crumble angel food cake into small pieces.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and milk.
Mix together until smooth.
Alternate in layers:
cake, strawberries and mixture.
End with mixture on top.
May add nuts to top.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Simmer.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and soda.
Beat and add bananas and nuts.
Bake in slow oven either in loaf pan or muffin pan.
This makes 12 large muffins.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In bowl, whisk together vinegar, oregano, basil, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Add the oil in a stream, whisking, and whisk the marinade well.
In a large resealable plastic bag, combine vegetables with marinade.
Seal the bag, pressing out excess air. Let marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning the bag several times.
Serve on a bed of torn lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breast of turkey filets(charcoal grilled)
directions: Debone the breast meat from 1 turkey.
Slice diagonally in 3/4-inch
slices.
Mix
olive oil, orange juice and garlic. Pour marinade over turkey.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours, turning meat several times.
Grill over charcoal fire for approximately 20 minutes
or
until cooked through.	Baste several times with remaining marinade.
Serve with plain or heated salsa.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Place all ingredients together in a large bowl and beat until smooth. Preheat oven to 325°. Pour cake mixture in 3 greased cake pans. Bake 20 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes in pans on a rack. Remove cake layers and cool completely before icing.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Prepare noodles; drain.
Cook onions gently in margarine. Stir in flour, salt and garlic powder.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and cottage cheese. Fold in salmon and noodles.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Mix 2 tablespoons margarine, melted, with bread crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn muffin casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with margarine in skillet. Bake at 350°.
Cooking times vary with dish used (glass baking dish
or cast-iron
skillet);
cook
approximately 35
to
40 minutes. Should be golden color on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *Use paper towels to absorb excess grease.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken until tender in well seasoned water.
Remove chicken and broth; measure 1 quart back into pan.
Bone and dice chicken and set aside.
Into broth, put celery, green pepper, onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Let cook a few minutes, then add spaghetti and cook until done.
Add tomatoes, olives, soup, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cheese to boned chicken, then add to spaghetti mixture.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: In saucepan blend sugar, cornstarch and salt; add milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Add well-beaten egg.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
In a shallow bowl or dish, layer wafers and bananas.
Pour pudding over while still warm.
Top with more wafers.
Serves 6.

title: egg quiche
directions: Microwave margarine, mushrooms and onion for 2 minutes.
Place 1/2 cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with mushroom-onion mixture; add ham and remaining cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
(May have to use mixer to mix in flour.)
Pour egg mixture over ingredients in dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 10 servings.

title: barbecue jackpot
directions: Brown beef; add rest of ingredients (except biscuits) to mixture of beef and mix well.
Put biscuits in a muffin pan and shape into a cup.
Put beef filling in cup, then Cheddar cheese, beef filling and top with Cheddar cheese.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
