directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in milk and egg yolks (slightly beaten).
Cook until thick and smooth (about 7 minutes), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oleo and coconut, blending well.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue, sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: tropical delight cake
directions: Going to make a recipe.

title: fluffy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Add ingredients together. Batter will be sticky. Transfer to lightly floured work surface. Use floured fingers to pat dough to 1-inch thickness. Use a 2 1/2-inch round biscuit cutter. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: cheese stuffed meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil a shallow baking pan with a little olive oil or pan spray.
Heat the olive oil in a frying pan over moderate heat.
Add onion; saute until golden (about 10 minutes). Combine the onion, ground beef, soy sauce and sage.
Divide the mixture into 8 portions.
Take a cube of cheese; cover with one portion of the mixture to form meatball.
Repeat with rest of cheese.
Place in baking pan; bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy rice
directions: Fry 3 tbsp. of uncooked rice until brown. Add peppers and onions and saute. Add rest of uncooked rice, salt and pepper, and tomatoes. Add a little water if its too dry. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: cajun party mix
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Pour over cereal, chips and nuts in large oven pan.
Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, stirring once every 15 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

title: jacquie's stromboli
directions: Brown ground turkey in a large skillet.
Mix in salsa and beans.
Simmer.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll out pizza crust in rectangle.
Put half the cheese in middle of crust.
Put meat mixture over cheese.
Put the rest of cheese on top.
Brush milk on outside edges of crust and fold over together.
Sprinkle corn meal on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix all other ingredients with the first mixture. Make golf ball size dough.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: pecan coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and set a rack in the middle level. Butter and flour Bundt pan.
Beat butter with sugar and vanilla until light, about 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating smooth between each addition.
Combine flour with baking soda and salt and stir well to mix.
Combine pecans and coconut and add a tablespoon of the flour mixture and rub between palms of hands to coat well.
Add the flour mixture alternately with the sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour batter into prepared pan and smooth top of batter.
Bake about 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool; wrap well.
Cake keeps well at room temperature 4 or 5 days.

title: vegetable and beef soup
directions: Cook meat until done.
Then add potatoes and onions and cook until tender.
Then add Bunker Hill beef and other vegetables. Cook until done.
(Soup like Sue Jones and Emma Jackson used to make.)

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt margarine or butter over low heat. Remove from stove and add the cocoa, flour, sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Mix in eggs, beating one at a time. Add nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool, then frost.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch square pan or any size will do.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put in refrigerator overnight.
(Be sure fruit is well drained.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour
sugar over apples and let stand about 30 minutes. Beat eggs.
Add
to
sugar and apples.
Add oil and beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased
and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Brown onion and bell pepper in tablespoon of oil and drain.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
No heart burn recipe!

title: great franks(hot dogs)
directions: Split hot dogs in half; insert slice of cheese and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon chopped onion.
Wrap a slice of bacon around hot dog and fasten with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp and brown. Broil 4 inches from heat.

title: german style pork chops
directions: Brown chops in frying pan; spoon sauerkraut over chops.
Top with brown sugar.
Place apples on top.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: jellied cherry cups
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Combine cherry syrup and lemon juice.
Add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Heat.
Pour over gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Add cherries, grapes, nuts and olives.
Shape cream cheese in ball of marble size.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Spoon into individual molds.
Chill until set.
Unmold on salad greens and serve with mayonnaise.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden country corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix corn and egg; add to dry ingredients, stirring lightly.
Heat small amount of oil in skillet.
Drop batter by tablespoons into skillet.
Fry about 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Makes 16 fritters.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut roast meat into small pieces and brown in a little oil. Add a little paprika to the meat while cooking.
Add the meat to potatoes, celery and carrots.
Add flour to the oil that the meat was in and add to stew.
Cook until tender.

title: yorkshire puddings
directions: Spray with cooking spray 8 sections of cupcake of muffin pan. Beat eggs with 1/4 cup milk only until blended.
In separate bowl beat 1 cup flour with 3/4 cup milk only.
Beat together to blend. Pour into pans.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve with roast beef and gravy.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, shortening and beat until like a cake. Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water. Add yeast and 2 cups water, then the flour. Let rise; shape rolls and bake. Can be refrigerated.

title: holiday cherries
directions: Wash and seed whole, ripe fruit.
Remove blossom end and all imperfections.
Put through food chopper (coarse blade).
Barely cover with cold water and cook until tender.
Measure and add equal amount of sugar.
Cook until thick over low heat.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together gently and pour in the pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruity rice krispies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat. Immediately add cereal.
Mix until well coated.
Press into a greased 13-inch x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: trifle
directions: Arrange slices of angel food cake in a dish; prepare jello according to package directions and pour over angel food cake. Chill until firm.
Add fruit cocktail.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Pour over fruit cocktail.
Cover with whipped topping.
Chill until served.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then blend in remaining ingredients.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: beef casserole
directions: Layer in order in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti creole
directions: Brown meat until no longer pink; drain.
Combine meat with tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and garlic in a saucepan.
Cook 45 minutes on medium heat.
Cook macaroni as directed.
Combine macaroni and meat sauce.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix together with a fork to distribute cheese.
Pour into a baking pan (9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inches).
Add a single layer of cheese slices to completely cover.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until heated through and cheese has melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes; slice hard-boiled eggs and put in with potatoes.
Mix onions with potatoes.
In small bowl, mix salad dressing, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Refrigerate prior to serving.
Enjoy.

title: gouda cheese ball
directions: Press crescent rolls together and roll into a circle twice the size of the Gouda.
Make sure to seal dough thoroughly to prevent cheese leakage.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or bake until golden brown.
Remove and let cool a bit before serving.
Cheese will be soft and warm inside the dough.

title: walnut parsley butter
directions: Mix.
Use with seafood, lamb, pork, veal, green beans, pasta. chicken kiev.

title: beef oven stew
directions: Cover tightly.
Bake 4 hours at 250°. You don't have to open to see if it is okay.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with blueberries.
Mix sugar and flour and mix with berries.
Put pineapple and juice evenly over blueberry mixture.
Sift cake mix evenly over it.
Take margarine and slice thin slices over the dry mix.
Try to cover it as much as possible.
You may add chopped pecans as a topping. Bake at 325° until crust is slightly brown.
If I have plenty of time, I like to bake very slowly (about 275°) and find that the mixture thickens better.
It may take 1 hour or so, but the top is still crunchy and the inside is a nice consistency, just right to eat with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.
You may add most any kind of fruit (not just blueberries).

title: mrs. kosanke's chinese green salad
directions: Drain vegetables and place in container.
Combine remaining ingredients and shake.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: stuffed winter squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place squash halves, cut side down in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir together apple, celery, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn squash halves cut side up.
Sprinkle with salt. Spoon apple mixture into halves.
Bake covered about 25 minutes more.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread
crescent
rolls onto an
ungreased 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Press to seal perforations.
Bake until golden brown; cool.

title: broccoli sweet salad
directions: Chop broccoli into bite size pieces, using only flowerettes. Mix broccoli, onion, bacon & cheese, tossing to mix well. In separate container, mix mayonnaise, sugar & red cider vinegar together. Just before serving pour over broccoli & mix well.

title: a.j.'s lemon pie
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons corn starch with 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add 4 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 tablespoon butter and three egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water very slowly. Cook until thick.
Cool.

title: biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients, oil, butter and milk, then add yeast mixture.
Refrigerate and use as needed.
Bake at 425°.

title: alice lake's chicken salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill and serve on sourdough bread, rye bread, in pita pockets or alone as a salad.

title: ann's easter pineapple torte
directions: Prepare crumb crust and set aside.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and lemon peel.
Drain juice from both cans pineapple into saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over top of juice.
Heat on low until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple to cream cheese mixture.
Stir gelatin into cream cheese mixture.
Thoroughly fold in Cool Whip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Soften cream
and
butter.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake at 450°
for 40 minutes.
Bacon bits make a great topping for this casserole.

title: low-fat mexitalian lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine chili, drained salsa, mushrooms, black olives, diced onion, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, stir together cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, chili mixture and Mozzarella cheese in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray. Repeat to make 3 layers.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lasagna is thoroughly heated.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry powders, then liquids, adding chocolate chips last. Bake in large Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not overbake.
(If Bundt pan has dark lining, decrease temperature to 325°.)

title: stuffed flounder fillet
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Place mixture in center of fillets; roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Place in baking dish, seam side down.
Place remaining ingredients on top of fillet.
Cover; bake for 20 minutes at 350°, or until done.
Serves 2.

title: quick moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in large bowl.
Place margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil; stirring constantly.
Pour into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients, saving the soda until last; mix well.
The sooner you get the cake into the oven after adding the soda, the better the cake.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together. Cover with ice water. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Heat to a good boil the remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Add to cucumber mixture.
Store in refrigerator or freezer. Best if not eaten for several days.

title: scallopine piccata
directions: Bone chicken breasts and pound thin.
In a bowl, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip cutlets in mixture and press firmly to coat. Shake off excess; chill.

title: vegetarian kabobs
directions: Cook tofu in a nonstick skillet for 4 to 5 minutes.
Transfer tofu to large bowl.
Add the squash, tomatoes, radishes and green pepper.
In small bowl stir together pineapple juice, lime juice, soy sauce, garlic, allspice and red pepper.
Pour over the tofu mixture until well coated.
Let stand for about 15 minutes.
Drain the tofu mixture, reserving the marinade.
Then gently thread the tofu and veggies onto 8 skewers.
Place kabobs on a nonstick broiling pan rack and brush them with remaining marinade.
Broil for about 8 to 10 minutes at about 4 inches from the heat.
May be served over a bed of rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl and mix well.
Mix flour, salt and soda; add gradually.
Add vanilla.
Mix apples and nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake is very moist.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate plunge fruit dip
directions: *Strawberries, banana, peaches, cantaloupe, raspberries, pineapple chunks, blackberries, etc.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion in a little oil and drain grease.
Add the other ingredients and simmer.
Serve on buns.

title: ma ma's stewed tomatoes
directions: Drop tomatoes in hot water and then in cold.
Peel.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Cook 4 hours.

title: p b & j feast
directions: Check bread for moldy spots.
Throw the slices in the air 2 times.
Upon landing, spread peanut butter on two slices with knife to 1/8-inch thickness.
Lick off knife (be careful!).
Use same knife to scoop jelly from jar; be generous.
(If peanut butter sticks to the roof of mouth, apply more jam in subsequent sandwiches.)
Slap two slices together, being careful not to spill any jam.
Cut sandwich in half diagonally.
Bring to mouth and eat entire sandwich in four bites.
Swallow with thankfulness and make another one.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Blend flour, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well; add sugar gradually.
Mix in oil; melt and add chocolate and vanilla to egg mixture.
Stir in all dry ingredients and nuts. Mix all together.
Put into greased 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and make into little balls.
Flatten slightly with a fork and bake at 375° until brown.

title: diet zucchini muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray muffin pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until browning.
Makes approximately 18 muffins.

title: barbecue beef and cheese sandwiches
directions: In skillet, cook onion and garlic in margarine.
Add ketchup, sugar, ReaLemon, Wyler's bouillon and mustard; simmer uncovered 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beef; heat through.
Spoon on buns.
Top with cheese slice.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Fabulous.

title: coffee pot punch
directions: In coffee pot place unsweetened pineapple juice, orange juice, apple juice and apricot juice.
In basket place brown sugar, whole cloves and cinnamon.
Perk until brown sugar is totally dissolved.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Add salt to rapidly boiling water.
Gradually add noodles so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until almost done.
Drain in colander.
Combine noodles, corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Mix lightly and turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Add cream cheese (crumble until it dissolves as much as possible).
Add 7-Up; stir in nuts and fruit.
Set.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush the pretzels; mix with the margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in long baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Save a little for topping.
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Add cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and spread on crust.
Mix Jell-O with 3 cups hot water.
Let partially jell and add frozen strawberries and pour on crust.
Sprinkle top with remaining pretzels and refrigerate.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix and dissolve jello and boiling water.
Add everything to jello.
Put in mold.
Allow approximately a whole day to set in refrigerator so it is firm for serving.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a dish.
Melt margarine in another dish.
Flatten biscuits and cut in half.
Dip biscuit in margarine, then roll in cinnamon mixture.
Twist and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes. Makes double the biscuit count.

title: fresh fruit combe
directions: Combine honey, lemon juice and cinnamon and mix well.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Combine the fruit.
Pour in chilled dressing just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish. Beat flour, sugar and milk to a smooth batter. Pour over melted butter. Do not stir. Empty fruit over the batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cut up round steaks into cubes.
Drop into crock-pot.
Empty dry soup mix and cans of soup into crock-pot.
Add water and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: summer swedish rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
Stir in honey, dry milk, orange peel, anise and caraway seeds.
Stir in 4 c. white flour to form a thick batter.
Beat well with a wooden spoon (100 strokes).
Cover and let rise 45 minutes in a warm place.

title: layered dinner casserole
directions: Put browned hamburger into bottom of casserole.
Add peas (with juice) and onion.
Alternate layers of potatoes and carrots, ending with potatoes on top.
Lastly pour tomato soup over top. Add a little water so liquid shows through from top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: russian tea
directions: Make tea with 2 cups boiling water.
Let steep 5 minutes. Strain tea.
Pour rest of water, tea, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar in a 6-quart saucepan.
Mix thoroughly.
Put cloves and cinnamon into a spice bag.
Break them up by beating with handle of knife or similar object.
Tie top of spice bag; add to tea mixture. Cook over medium heat until steamy.
Do not bring to a boil.
Leave spice bag in tea 1 to 2 hours, depending on how spicy you want the tea.
Serve tea hot.

title: chocolate pie 2
directions: In a double boiler, add beaten egg yolks, sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes). Then add chocolate and butter and cook two minutes longer.
Pour into baked pie crust shell.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix green onions with cheeses; mix in one half of the chipped beef.
Add sauces and other ingredients; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in remainder of chipped beef until well covered.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Chop the veggies small and layer in order in a cake pan. Cover with 1/4 to 1/2-inch of mayonnaise. Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer.
Use as much mayonnaise as you wish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place chicken.
Add soup for next layer. Mix chicken broth and stuffing mix to desired consistency for top layer.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Bake butter flavored cake mix in 2 round cake pans as directed on package. Cool and split both round cakes to make 4 layers. Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut. Set aside a separate cup of mixture for last layer to frost. Frost cake between all layers. For top and sides, mix last cup of sour cream mixture that was set aside and 8 ounces Cool Whip and frost the rest of cake. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 days or more for best flavor!

title: p. w. favorite dessert
directions: Prepare lemonade with water as directed on the can.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of lemonade.
Add pudding plus 1 3/4 cups of lemonade.
Cook and stir until thickens, then cool.
Whip Dream Whip and add to the cooked mixture.
Add other drained ingredients and let set in refrigerator.

title: family favorite casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and green beans each according to package directions.
Drain.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix together. Stir in soup and 2 cups of the cheese.
Pour half the mixture into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 can onions.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture and one cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip specials
directions: Spray baking sheets lightly and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs. Add 1/2 c. mayonnaise, salt, and pepper; mix together. Cut eggs in halves. Mix the egg yolks with the mayonnaise. Sprinkle tops with paprika. Chill and serve.

title: quick lunch box cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts, into a large bowl. Blend at lowest speed on mixer.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour butter into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate banana drop cookies(diabetic)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Cream together butter, vanilla, water, eggs and Sucaryl until creamy and smooth.
Add flour mixture and mashed bananas alternately, mixing until well blended.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Stir several times during refrigeration.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the crumbs, 2 tablespoons of sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: english pea dumplings
directions: In a large saucepan, combine peas, milk and butter.
Heat to almost boiling.
Drop dumplings gently into mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Reduce to medium-low heat and cook for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: spinach fettucine
directions: Remove and discard tough stems from spinach. Tear or coarsely chop leaves.
In pan, cook garlic and onion in half the butter until golden. Add spinach. Cover and cook until just wilted.

title: bean salad
directions: Put chickpeas, green beans and yellow beans in mixing bowl. In small bowl, mix well with whisk the shallots, mustard, garlic, vinegar and oil until thick.

title: baby food cake
directions: *Self-rising flour is all-purpose flour with 1 1/2 teaspoons of baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon of salt added per cup of flour.

title: chicken penne
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Marinate the chicken breasts 1 to 2 hours.
Broil chicken breasts until cooked through, then cut into pieces. Combine with marinade.
Heat and toss with cooked pasta.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: apple torte
directions: About 3 hours before serving or early in day: In large bowl, combine yeast, sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and whole-wheat flour.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat margarine or butter and 1 1/2 cups milk until very warm (125° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt completely.

title: dump it cake
directions: Dump your Thank You brand flavors in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cake mix on top of the fruit.
Drizzle the butter over the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° until light brown and the fruit bubbles out the sides.

title: apple nut pie
directions: Mix ingredients, except nutmeg and apple pie spice.
Sprinkle nutmeg and apple pie spice on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in 9 or 10-inch pie shell.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, water, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Boil 2 to 3 hours, until thick.
Add cheese and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Mix sauce and spaghetti.
Pour into greased pan and spread cream of mushroom soup over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Dice eggplant.
Finely chop celery, carrot and onion.
In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot olive oil, stir eggplant, celery, carrot and onion; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are almost tender.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, sugar and salt; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until a dough like mixture is formed. Shape into balls by the spoonful.
Sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar or cover with melted chocolate.

title: oven-fried potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes real well; cut them into small wedges.
Place the wedges, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Brush wedges with 1/2 the oil mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Brush occasionally with remaining oil.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop out the pulp. Resreve the skins.
Chop pulp and onion.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add pulp, onion and spices.
Add ground beef until browned.
Add tomato sauce.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix catsup, steak sauce and honey in a small bowl.
Pour over pork chops. Bake, covered with foil, at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: scotch scones
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar. Mix thoroughly with knife, then gradually pour in milk while you stir until all are combined.

Makes a wet dough. Sift plenty of flour on a board. Turn the dough out in the center of floured patch using a knife to scrape it all out. Sift more flour on top of dough and pat out until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 12 or 15 pieces any shape. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Be sure oven is 275°.
Bake at least 35 minutes.
They must be baked slowly in order that dough raises before a crust is formed. When touched on top and they spring back, they are done. Scones should be white, even when they are done.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator at least four hours.
You can take these out, put in muffin pan and bake as you wish.
This mix will keep as long as two weeks in refrigerator.

title: sorenson's cheese and beer fondue
directions: Heat beer slowly with garlic.
Toss cheese with flour and pepper.
When beer is hot, add a little cheese at a time until melted, stirring as cheese is added.
Cut French bread into cubes with crust on all pieces.
Dip cubes into cheese.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux of flour and oil.
Brown over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and paste, mix well and cook about 5 minutes.
Add water.
Let simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp, cook about 20 minutes.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, alternately, with sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in fruit and nuts. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours at 300°.

title: "3" bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients and beans.
Marinate overnight out of refrigerator.
Chill before serving.
Keeps well.

title: angel cupcakes
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend in butter and slowly add 2/3 cup of the milk to which vanilla has been added.
Beat for 3 minutes and add remaining milk and eggs.
Beat for an additional 3 minutes.
Fill 12 greased and floured 3-inch cupcake tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 cupcakes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Remove seeds and cut zucchini in strips.
Cook in water until done, but crunchy.
Drain.
Saute onion in oil until tender. Drain.

title: cream cheese frosting(for carrot cake)
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter. Cream until smooth. Add powdered sugar. Stir in vanilla.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan; refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and other desired taco toppings (tomatoes, lettuce, etc.)
Serve with taco chips.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Roll cracker crumbs.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then gradually beat sugar into egg whites.
Fold in crumbs, flavoring, pecans and baking powder.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles(8 pints)
directions: Do not peel cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers, then add onions, peppers, garlic and salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix.
Let stand for 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Heat to a boil; seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients (Parmesan cheese goes in last).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: michigan pea and peanut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: quick-chick waldorf salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve on bed of lettuce with crackers.

title: sausage-brown rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Stir in rice, milk, celery, green pepper, onion, soup and mushrooms.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon shortcake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter. To beaten egg, add milk and blend into flour mixture.
Divide dough into two pieces and roll each piece 1/3-inch thick in a circle shape.
Blend together salmon, mayonnaise, parsley, onion, pickle, salt and pepper.
Place one shortcake on greased baking sheet; spread with filling.
Cover with other shortcake and bake in hot (425°) oven for about 20 minutes or until done.
Melt cheese for sauce on top.

title: sausage-onion ball
directions: Crumble raw sausage.
Add grated cheese and onion.
Mix in Bisquick.
Make small balls and bake on foil covered pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dreambar
directions: Place stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and heat until melted.
Place crushed graham crackers in the bottom of pan evenly, then add sweetened condensed milk evenly.
Add chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, walnuts (crushed) and coconut flakes. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown, in oven at 350°.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cut meat into small cubes or cook meat until tender before adding vegetables.
Use large cooker; cover and simmer until tender, about 3 hours.
Season to taste.
Add parsley just before serving.

title: fresh mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter and lemon juice for 4 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook slowly, stirring, for 1 minute. Add sour cream, dill, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir 1 minute. Serve warm on toast.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: spicy pepper jelly(makes 3 pints)
directions: Whirl peppers in blender until finely chopped.
Pour into 5-quart pan and stir in vinegar and sugar until well blended. Boil, stirring constantly.
Pour in pectin at once and return to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook uncovered stirring until thick (3 minutes).
Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Pour into hot sterilized jelly jars.
Fill to 1/8 of rim.
Wipe rim clean.
Top with sterile lids; screw on bands.
Let cool from drafts; test seal.
If unsealed put in refrigerator and use within a month.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix everything together and bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: cream cheese pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar together.
Pour into 8-inch graham cracker crusts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour over ingredients and bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle sliced almonds first, then cinnamon (as much as desired) over top of pie.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Let cool; refrigerate when not serving.

title: pamona lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and oil and beat 10 minutes. Cook 1 hour in stem pan at 250°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add rice and broccoli to well blended sauce (soup and cheese).
Fold in water chestnuts. Pour into a well buttered or Pam-sprayed casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit well; mix with sour cream.

title: mexican supper
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in skillet until light brown. Drain.
Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper. Layer half each of cheese, celery, olives and half of the noodles from main dish package on beef.
Repeat.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, corn and bacon drippings.
Set aside.
Saute ground meat and drain.
Separately prepare 1 large onion, cheese and jalapenos and mix together. Pour into greased skillet (heated) with a fine layer of corn meal sprinkled and browned.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven or until springs back.

title: baton rouge cake(no eggs, no mixer)
directions: Mix with spoon the sugar, oil and crushed pineapple.
Mix flour and spices separately.
Stir in applesauce.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add in diced bananas and nuts.
Gently stir and pour in a greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
The aroma and taste is wonderful!
This cake never fails and keeps moist for days.

title: hobo sandwich
directions: Place in aluminum foil.
Cook at 300° for one hour.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Mix other ingredients with ground chuck; simmer together on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: eva's sandwich spread
directions: Grind together the eggs, Spam, carrots and onion, then add salad dressing, vinegar and sugar.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend and refrigerate.
Make a few hours ahead of time.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Mix and spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425°. Melt 1/2 stick margarine and 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt and brush on biscuits while hot.

title: mom's no guilt quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine egg and all vegetables.
Stir. Add cheese and stir again.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Test doneness by inserting knife in center of quiche.
If knife comes out clean, quiche is done.
Otherwise return to oven and check again in 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with warm breadsticks.

title: tuna scallop royale
directions: Cut each avocado into halves lengthwise.
Remove seed and sprinkle with salt.
Combine undiluted soup and tuna and heat thoroughly.

title: brown sugar dip for fruit
directions: Serve with apple or pear slices.
Great with bananas also.

title: turtle cake
directions: Blend the cake mix, 1 cup milk and butter until smooth. Spread half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in remaining milk and spread over top of warm cake.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top of caramel mixture.
Spread rest of cake batter on top.
Bake at 350° for another 15 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: lima bean medley(low calorie)
directions: In large non-stick skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Stir in Lima Beans and corns.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in the basil, salt, and pepper.
Yields 4 Servings, 2 Points.

title: jalapeo cornbread
directions: Heat an 8-inch cast-iron skillet in a 400° oven for 5 minutes. Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Set aside. Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened. Remove skillet from oven and coat with cooking spray; pour batter into hot skillet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 8 servings.

title: creamy chicken enchilada stack
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl combine soup, sour cream and chilies.
In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, spread 1/4 of the soup mixture.
Top with 2 tortillas, 1/3 of cheese and 1/3 olives. Repeat with remaining ingredients, ending with cheese and olives. Bake 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed and add 1 cup sugar.
Let start to gel, then add cranberries (uncooked and chopped fine), pecans, orange and apple (cut up).
Let gel.

title: banana butter
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly; measure 4 cups into 6 or 8-quart saucepot.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add fruit protector if desired. Prepare jars; keep jars and lids hot until ready to fill.
Measure sugar into a separate bowl.
Stir pectin into fruit in saucepot. Add margarine.
Place over heat; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in all sugar.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon.
Ladle quickly into prepared jars, filling to within 1/8-inch of tops.
Wipe jar rims and threads.
Cover with two-piece lids.
Screw bands tightly. Invert jars for 5 minutes, then turn upright.
After jars cool, check seals.

title: sweet snack mix
directions: Mix cinnamon, maple flavoring, brown sugar and margarine in bowl.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix cereals, oysters crackers, peanuts, pretzels, and pecans.
Pour brown sugar mixture
over dry ingredients and toss well.
Put a thin layer on cookie sheet and bake
at 250° for one hour, or until dry.
Stir occasionally during baking.
Cool.
Store in air tight containers.

title: beef tongue(sounds gross, tastes great)
directions: Wash tongue well.
Place in roaster.
Fill 3/4 full with water.
Cover and boil for 3 hours.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups water. Rinse meat under cold water (until it is cool enough to handle). Peel off skin.
Return meat to roaster with reserved 1 1/2 cups water.
Season to taste and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Chill completely.
Slice thin and serve on a luncheon tray.

title: millionaire clusters
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Stir and add pecan halves.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let stand about 1 hour until firm.
Then dip in following chocolate mixture.
Mix in double boiler the Hershey bar and paraffin.

title: holiday bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add all ingredients.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant.
Boil until tender or transparent; drain. Saute bread crumbs in butter.
Saute ground meat and diced onion in frying pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: green beans and broccoli casserole(ingredients for 10 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Cook green beans and broccoli according to package directions. Drain well and place in baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with cheese. Bake 45 minutes.

title: paglione's spaghetti sauce
directions: In saucepot, saute the chopped onion and garlic in the olive oil.
When the onion is translucent, add the meat you are using for your sauce.
(Meatballs should be added later so they won't be hard.)
When meat is browned on the outside, add the crushed tomatoes can, plus 1 can of water.
Add the tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 2 hours and add the basil and oregano.
At this time, you can put in your meatballs to cook for another half hour.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk. Layer ingredients. Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: nancy everhart's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco together; add eggs.
Add the buttermilk with the lemon flavoring.
Add flour with soda and salt.
Beat, beat, beat!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine; stir well. Press in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven; let cool on a wire rack.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding per directions on box.
With mixer blend in cream cheese, fold in Cool Whip, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Crumble a few vanilla wafers on top for garnish.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Sprinkle on garlic salt.
Mix all ingredients, but Parmesan cheese.
Pour on chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be served with rice.

title: crab and pasta
directions: Heat soup, stirring, until smooth.
Add butter and milk.
When hot, remove from heat; stir in cheese, reserving some to sprinkle on top.
Combine cheese sauce, pasta, crabmeat and pepper.
Spoon into greased shallow casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: camper's special
directions: Chop up potatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Fry in 1/4 cup grease until almost done.
Stir in eggs, chopped Spam and seasonings.
Cook for about 10 more minutes or until eggs are done.
Serves 6.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix soda, jam and buttermilk; add sifted flour and spices alternately with buttermilk and soda; add raisins and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350°.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat with the onions. Drain well. Add all ingredients except kidney beans and cook 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and cook 1/2 hour longer.
This is hot chili.
Freezes well.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in
2 cups hot water.
Add frozen strawberries; stir occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple with juice and bananas.
Serve with sour cream dressing or Dream Whip.

title: mashed potatoes with goat cheese(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: turtles
directions: Melt milk with caramels in double boiler.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Arrange 3 pecans on buttered foil and spoon caramel over. Let stand 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and let stand 10 minutes.
Spoon over caramel and nut mixture.

title: russian tea
directions: Slice lemon and oranges thin.
Cover with sugar.
Let stand one hour.
Make tea with 4 cups water.
Let steep 3 minutes. Strain tea over fruit.
Add clove and cinnamon.
Add water. Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and cider together; bring to a boil. Remove from heat for 5 minutes; add Certo.
Pour into 1/2 pint jars and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together in crock-pot; cook on low for 4 hours.

title: tansirs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together until a soft dough forms. Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough into small balls; press into mini cupcake pans.
Put some nuts into each one.
Make filling with remaining ingredients.
Fill cuplets 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll into balls. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown, depending on size of balls, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: basic rolls
directions: Pour into 2 well-greased and sugared loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: quick fudge icing
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together 3 minutes. Cool until lukewarm. Add the vanilla and powdered sugar to desired spreading consistency. Chopped pecans may be added, if desired.

title: apple turnover
directions: Slice apples on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients to make batter and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies and add butter.
Mix well and press in the bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Cream together until smooth the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over the cookies and return the pan to the refrigerator.
Prepare the chocolate pudding with 3 1/2 cups of milk.
Do not use 4 cups.
Pour pudding on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip over the pudding and sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: super french toast
directions: The night before, beat eggs in large bowl.
Add orange juice, Grand Marnier, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and orange peel; mix well.
Dip bread into mixture, turning to coat all surfaces. Transfer bread to baking dish in a single layer.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning mixture occasionally until liquid is absorbed into bread.

title: creamed corn corn bread
directions: Saute pepper and onion.
Mix all except sour cream and cheese and put in greased casserole.
Cover with sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix together the Jell-O, hot water, 7-Up, crushed pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Allow to soft set.
Cook together the saved pineapple juice (add water if necessary to equal 1/2 cup), the sugar, flour and egg.
Thicken over medium heat; cool.

title: hot caramel sauce
directions: Cook until a full boil.
Take off stove; pour over cake.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Wash chops and place in a baking pan.
Season with seasoning salt.
Pour Pepsi and an equal amount of tomato juice over meat. Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
This is Cecil's favorite.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 1 minute, then add oats and peanut butter while boiling.
Beat and drop on wax paper or cabinet top with a spoon. (Coconut can be used instead of peanut butter.)

title: no peek casserole
directions: Put meat and soups in a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish, cover and bake in a 350° oven for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles or cooked rice.

title: gold salad
directions: Put together lemon and orange jello, hot water and lemon juice.
Set until halfway jelled.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows; let jell.
Combine pineapple juice (add water to equal the 1 cup), egg, sugar and flour.
Cook until mixture is of custard consistency.
Add margarine and stir until margarine melts completely and blends in.
Let cool; add whipped cream or Cool Whip (to equal whipped cream).
Spread on jello and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces. Melt margarine; crush crackers. Add all other ingredients. Dip chicken in margarine and roll in crumb mix. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix the soup, milk and grated cheese (I use at least a cup here) together.
Roll out crescent rolls.
Put chicken on each roll.
Roll these up and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour soup mixture over rolls.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes or until rolls are brown.
Last 5 minutes or so I like to top with more grated cheese.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour mixture until all flour is damp.
Refrigerate before using.
Do not roll out!
Simply pinch and roll amount needed.
Handle very lightly! Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes (or until brown).
Dough can be kept 1 week if covered in refrigerator!

title: berlinerkranser
directions: Add the minced yolks to the raw yolks that have been well beaten.
Wash butter to remove salt; add sugar and cream well. Combine egg and flour mixtures.
Take small piece of dough and roll into the size of a pencil.
Shape into small wreaths.
Dip wreaths into slightly beaten egg whites and then into crushed Domino sugar.
Bake in 375° oven until delicate brown.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all together in pie plate.
Sprinkle with a little more parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375 for 30 minutes or until lightly browned or bubbly.
Serve with Ritz or other butter crackers.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into about 2-inch squares while warm.
Makes 16 cookies.

title: chess cake
directions: Heat margarine and brown sugar on low heat.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients in order.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 pan at 300 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool, but while still lightly warm, cut into pieces and roll in powdered sugar.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat with onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Total prep time:
20 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3/4 cup margarine with 3 tablespoons of brown sugar. Mix with 2 1/2 cups crushed (not too fine) pretzels.
Pat into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pinwheel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and 1 cup Carnation milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, vanilla and remaining 1/4 cup milk; beat until blended.
Add melted chocolate.
Pour into layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and split to form 4 layers.
Frost with Pinwheel Frosting.

title: cheese spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal and boiling water; stir until smooth.
Stir in soup, cream, cheese, egg yolks, margarine, onion and salt. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate philly cookies
directions: Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb in middle.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fluffy fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour into cooled pie shell. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small pieces.
This will take approximately 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook 4 weeks at 375°, or until you run out of fuel.
If lots of people are expected, add 2 rabbits, but do this only if necessary, because some people don't like to find hare in their stew.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in confectioners sugar, then the egg and vanilla extract.
Sift together flour and baking soda and stir into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and arrange 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press each ball down with the tines of a fork.
Bake for about 6 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Put cucumbers in salt brine (salt in water) to draw them for approximately 45 minutes; drain and rinse.
Add onions.

title: dream sickle punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, sherbet and ice cream together until smooth. Put in ginger ale before serving.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding apples last.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
When light brown, turn over.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar or serve with maple syrup.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: slum maguligan
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings. Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain macaroni and add to the meat mixture.
Stir in tomato soup.
Add half of the cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with the remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk. On medium heat, stirring constantly, heat until thick and smooth. Cook macaroni as directed on box and drain.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut roast or steak into cubes.
Mix together dry onion soup and water.
Pour the mixture over meat.
Bake in a covered casserole for 3 hours at 375°.
Uncover.
Add mushrooms.
Heat for another 10 minutes.
Serve on buttered noodles.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla (or almond) extract.
Add walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Scale 24 servings per 12 x 10 x 2-inch pan (9 x 13-inch). 48 servings per 12 x 20 x 2-inch pan (cut 4 x 8-inch).
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (325° for 6 minutes, convection).
Mix cream cheese, milk, pudding mix together; spread over cooled crust.
Whip topping, fold in powdered sugar.
Spread on top of pudding mixture.
Chill to firm.

title: bacon-wrapped chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon strips in thirds.
Wrap each strip around a water chestnut and poke with toothpick to hold.
Set single layer in glass dish or cake pan.
Heat in oven for 20 minutes at 400°. Remove and drain.
Combine 3 other ingredients and pour on chestnuts.
Return to oven for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: paprika steak and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle steak pieces with meat tenderizer. Pound with mallet to tenderize meat.
Melt Crisco in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add sliced onion and paprika.
Simmer until onion is soft and tender.
Add steak pieces; brown on both sides, then cover with water.
Add beef bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down; simmer for 1/2 hour or so.
Peel and cut potatoes. After meat has cooked for 1/2 hour, add potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate syrup icing
directions: Blend together the sugar and cocoa. Cook all ingredients on medium heat until thick.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool slightly.
Poke holes in cake and pour 1/2 cup rum or Kahlua over top.
Let stand overnight.
Add a little more liquor in the morning.

title: no-roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar and powdered sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls; place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Dip a flat bottomed glass in sugar; flatten cookies to 1/4 inch thickness.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until cookies are set, but not brown.
Remove cookies to wire rack to cool.
Yield about 6 dozen.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is baking, combine pineapple and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
When cake is done, punch holes in top of cake with a fork.
You can add coconut and pecans to the pineapple mixture or it can be omitted.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Chill.
Mix pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla. Stir in nuts. Sift soda, salt and flour together and add to creamed mixture. Stir in oatmeal. Divide into 3 equal parts and roll each into a log in wax paper (will be soft). Chill until firm. Slice thin (1/4-inch) and place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugars; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well; add oatmeal, then dry ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Take juice from cherries; add with water to make 2 cups.
Put in pan along with sugar, lard and raisins. Bring to boil; cool. Add eggs and rest of ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 or 3 loaves.

title: uncooked tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion, garlic and basil finely.
Add oil, salt and pepper.
Let stand 1 hour to use fresh, or pack into containers and freeze.
Before serving, heat, stirring.
Adjust seasoning.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Drain crab meat.
Mix with other ingredients into sour cream. Mix until smooth.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: sparkling pink party punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 32 cups.

title: old-fashion egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat together well. Add hot milk; mix well. Pour into large deep-dish pie shell or 2 small pie shells. Sprinkle tops with nutmeg and bake until the consistency of Jell-O or knife comes out clean when inserted. Bake the first 15 minutes at 450°, then at 350° to finish, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter/shortening together.
Add eggs, beating in one at the time.
Pour in greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake one hour at 325° or until done.

title: catherine's layer salad
directions: Fill a large bowl or baking pan half full of sliced lettuce, fluffed up.
Add, in layers: celery, green pepper and onion.
Add frozen peas which have been cooked, drained and cooled.
Spread mayonnaise over the top.
Sprinkle sugar over the mayonnaise. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Fry, drain and crumble bacon over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnite.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
For 1/2 recipe, use a 10-inch pie plate.

title: apple lollipops
directions: Will need 1 package wooden meat skewers.

title: lemonade for 100
directions: Boil 4 cups water with sugar for 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice. Stir in pineapple or juice concentrate.
Add oranges and 4 gallons of water and chill overnight.
Serve over ice.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries overnight.
Mix 4x sugar, cream cheese and oleo until stiff.
Put the sugar mixture around the cherries.
When all the cherries are covered, store in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Roll covered cherries with melted chocolate.
Take out, place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir well until cheese melts.
Spread on rye, pumpernickel or the mini bagels.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in large plastic bag in freezer.
Broil 6 minutes before serving.
Makes lots.

title: excellent salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend very well.
Toss over and through salad.

title: fiesta beef
directions: Saute beef, onion, chilies and garlic in oil in a skillet until beef is browned.
Add chili powder, tomatoes, salt and water.
Break up tomatoes.
Bring to boil and stir rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and parsley.

title: chocolate drop candy
directions: Melt chocolate; add condensed milk and pinch of salt.
Remove from heat and add cup of marshmallows (miniature do not absorb chocolate as well).
Add nuts.
Drop by spoon and allow to cool and set.

title: flossie johnsons beets
directions: Boil all ingredients except beets.
Pour mixture over beets, which have been packed in sterile, hot jars.
Seal and process for about 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: late summer soup
directions: The secret to the rich flavor of this low calorie vegetable soup is to saute the onions just enough to bring out its natural sweetness and not to overcook the other vegetables.
Heat oil over medium heat; add onions.
Saute 5 minutes or until softened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer soup 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In food processor, puree 2 1/2 cups soup.
Pour into pan and heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cut carrots into slices and boil
with sugar until tender. Drain and cool.
Alternate layers of carrots with slices of green pepper and onion rings. Blend together the tomato soup, vinegar, oil and 1 c sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. Keeps indefinitely.

title: sourdough corn bread
directions: Mix sourdough, powdered milk and warm water with flour in a large bowl.
Set in warm place 3 to 4 hours.
In small bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Pour over starter mix.
Add cornmeal, salt and soda.
Fold ingredients into starter mix until well blended; do not beat.
For thick bread, pour into an 8-inch square pan.
For thin bread, pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: granny birdie's zucchini marmalade
directions: In a large bowl, cut up zucchini in small pieces.
Fill bowl. Cut up the oranges (discard ends and seeds).
Do the same with the lemon, rind and all, cut small.
Pour the sugar over it and let it set, covered, for 24 hours.
Cook until desired thickness.
Jar, seal and enjoy.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Add enough evaporated milk until smooth.
Pour over cabbage.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes into small pieces.
Boil potatoes until tender and mash.
Add eggs, sugar, and milk.
Stir until blended.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, and raisins.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven and layer top with mini-marshmallows.
Bake casserole until marshmallows are melted.

title: peppermint schnapps
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Add Everclear and peppermint extract.
Makes 8 pints.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain and squeeze.
Combine all ingredients with spinach and mix well.
Make 3/4-inch balls. Bake at 325° on greased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cucumber squares
directions: Cream together the cream cheese with a very little milk to make spreadable.
Add salad dressing mix.
Spread on the bread. Cut into 4 squares.
Lay a slice of cucumber on each square. Place plastic wrap between each layer of bread on serving plate. Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and boil 4 to 5 potatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Place onions in bacon grease and cook until transparent.
Mix other ingredients and add to onions in pan.
Simmer until thick.
Add potatoes and simmer until thoroughly mixed.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix leak soup mix, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Let chill for at least 2 hours.
Add chopped onion and spinach to sour cream mixture.
Serve with Hawaiian bread, crackers or corn chips.

title: danish dessert
directions: Combine water, Kool-Aid, clear jell and sugar in a saucepan. Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in jello.
Fold in strawberries. Chill.

title: fruit topped cheesecake(cheesecake is a great dessert.)
directions: Mix well, all ingredients, except for the sour cream.
Pour into a graham cracker crust shell and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Remove cheesecake, but do not turn off oven.
Pour sour cream on top and return to oven for 5 more minutes.
Let cake cool, then top with 1 can of pie filling such as blueberry, cherry or strawberry.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Dice onion and brown together with meat in skillet.
Mix all the other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix raisins, sugar, butter, egg yolks, vanilla and beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit whip salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly.
Pour dry jello over the Cool Whip, mix well.
Add cottage cheese and pour into a mold.
Let set in refrigerator until serving time.
Unmold and serve.
Serves 8.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix and chill. Serve with vegetables and/or chips.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, lemon juice and walnuts in medium bowl.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans lengthwise into 4 hot pint canning jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
To each jar, add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1/4 tablespoon red pepper flakes, 1 garlic clove and 1 head dill.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in baking dish. Pour cake mix over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour this over cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: hamburger-macaroni and cheese dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on package. Brown meat and drain. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Combine ingredients.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: slow cooker taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker and cook on low setting for 8 hours.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: About 1 hour before serving or early in day, preheat oven to 350°.
Spray eight 6-ounce brioche pans or jumbo muffin pan cups (3 x 1 1/2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Place the prepared brioche pans in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan for easier handling.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Can keep up to 2 weeks.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Combine ingredients to taste.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into three equal parts and freeze in freezer bags overnight.
When you are ready for punch, just add 2 quarts ginger ale to each bag.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in Italian dressing 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; bake until melted and bubbly, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Cover.
Chill.
Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 8x11 1/2 inch pan.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown (23-25 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown chopped beef.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Drain off fat, if desired.
Blend beef, onion, garbanzo beans, chili, shredded cheese, ripe olives, salsa and Catalina salad dressing. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add 1 pound salad greens, mixing well with ingredients.
Top with taco corn chips or chili corn cheese chips and serve.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: apricot chicken breast(cat. passover)
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Rinse with cold water and pat dry.
Combine matzo meal with ginger, garlic powder, salt and pepper in shallow dish.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix 1 box Jell-O and let congeal.
Spread sour cream over top of Jell-O.
Slice bananas on top of sour cream, then slice strawberries on top of bananas.
Mix other box of Jell-O and let cool.
Pour on top and chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Sprinkle corn flakes over bottom of casserole dish. Cut up cabbage and place on top of corn flakes to the rim of the dish. Blend milk, mayonnaise and celery soup with wire whisk. Pour over the cabbage. Sprinkle grated cheese over top of the cabbage, then more crushed corn flakes over cheese. Pour melted margarine over all. Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place washed and cleaned strawberries in pie shell.
Cook Junket according to package directions for pie filling.
Take off heat.
Add strawberry jello; mix well.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: whole wheat orange peanut butter cookies
directions: In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In large bowl, beat together margarine and peanut butter; beat in egg, orange rind and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Flatten with sugared fork.
Bake at 350° about 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli over low heat and drain.
Mix cheese, soup and pepper.
Add broccoli; cook over low heat for 1 more minute.
Add almonds and mushrooms.
Stir.
Keep in fondue pot or chafing dish. Dip with Fritos.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer and set aside.
Melt butter; add sesame seed and brown slightly.
Add coffee, soy sauce, Worcestershire, vinegar and onion.
Pour over roast and let stand at room temperature for at least 12 hours.
Turn meat often. Remove from marinade and grill, basting frequently with marinade. Can use other cuts of meat.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Heat oil in skillet (1/4 inch deep).
Put tortilla in oil until it starts to puff and immediately turn tortilla over.
Take out and drain on paper towel.
Repeat with all tortillas.
Put grated cheese on each tortilla and roll up.
Place in 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cover with chili and top with more grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Tortillas can be filled with additional toppings such as onions, seasoned ground beef, chicken, etc.

title: chicken-pineapple salad
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Serve on bread, pita bread or on lettuce.

title: strawberry dream cake(origin: unknown)
directions: Mix together cake mix, flour, gelatin, eggs and water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add strawberries, including juice to mixture.
Beat 1 minute. Add oil and beat 1 more minute. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans and continue cooling on rack.

title: chocolate shortbread logs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Using 1 teaspoon dough for each cookie, shape with hands into 2-inch logs. Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: party cheesecakes
directions: You will also need paper muffin liners.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Stir in pineapple and milk. Add cubed bread (fold in). Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350°, covered, 1/2 hour and uncovered, 1/2 hour.

title: date nut bread
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together dates, baking soda and boiling water; set aside and let cool. Sift flour and salt together in another bowl. Cream together butter, sugar and eggs; add date mixture after it has cooled, then gradually add flour/salt mixture, scraping bowl often. Add vanilla and mix in nuts. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 6 small pans (fill pans about halfway). Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Small loaves will bake in less time, about 40 minutes. Remove loaves from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted ingredients.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Roll out with 1 additional cup flour.
Working it into the dough, gradually roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cookies.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Take round steak and onions, brown it.
Add beans, ravioli and cheese.
Cook slowly on top of stove, about 30 minutes.
Serve with French bread with grated cheese on top.

title: lorraine's fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly while boiling, then remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips or morsels and vanilla.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square pan that has been lined with foil.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, Karo, butter, vanilla and salt.
Put pecans in bottom of pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then at 325° until knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 35 to 40 minutes).

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil together last 6 ingredients.
Pour over cukes and onions. Let cool.
Put in large container with lid.
Keep in refrigerator until used.
(Will keep up to a year if they last that long.)

title: bacon-vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except lettuce.
Pour dressing over all and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, add lettuce.

title: creamy caramel icing
directions: Bring sugar, cream and butter to a boil.
Boil 6 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy and of spreading consistency.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: lazy day stew(club member: john waters)
directions: Cook beef and onions in large saucepan until lightly browned; drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Simmer for about 40 minutes, adding tomato juice or water if moisture evaporates. Add cheese; cook until melted. Serve hot.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spread over pizza crust and add desired ingredients to complete pizza.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Mix milk, instant pudding and whipped topping.
Combine both mixtures together.

title: olive filled cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter together and add enough water to make a pie-like dough.
Take small amounts of dough, about the size of a walnut and form around an olive.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. May be frozen and kept indefinitely before cooking.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Then add fruits: cherries and dates, then pecans.
Chill at least one hour.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven until lightly browned.

title: parsley cakes
directions: Combine first five ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add seasonings and mold into patties.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs; fry in deep fat at 350° until browned.
Serve with cold tartar sauce.

title: chicken divan
directions: Partially cook chicken.
If using fresh vegetables, partially cook also.
If using frozen bag of vegetables, just thaw. Cook noodles.

Place chicken in bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with margarine. Top alternately, noodles, vegetables and soup (set aside 1 can of soup to mix with some cheese), ending up with vegetables on top.
Top with 1 can of soup
mixed with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company ham and noodles
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add ham; cook and stir until heated through.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low, gradually stir in sour cream.
Add the mushrooms, cook and stir until thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage(kaposzta)
directions: Fill large pot half full of salted water.
Core cabbage and place in water to boil.
Keep turning cabbage every 10 minutes until leaves appear wilted and falling off and center of head seems done or soft.
Drain.
Pull leaves off and trim thick center vein from each cabbage leaf.
Set cabbage leaves aside to cool.
Add water to the rice in a separate bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, add beef, onions, salt, pepper, paprika and eggs.
Drain rice and add to beef mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place 1 large tablespoon of meat mixture into each cabbage leaf.
Roll up and tuck both ends in to make a neat roll.
Rinse sauerkraut in strainer with cold water and let drain.
Place cabbage rolls in a Dutch oven close together in layers.
Pour tomatoes, sauce, sauerkraut and kolbasz on top. Add enough water to cover.
Cover the pot and let cook 2 hours or until tested as done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Let all this cook together slowly for several hours.

title: st. nicks cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Sift flour and salt; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.
Shape into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cook until set, not brown.
Roll in xxx sugar while hot.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup of syrup.
Mix pineapple, reserved syrup, 1/3 cup of sugar and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring, until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat; add lemon peel. Cool.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup of sugar. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Spoon pineapple mixture into pie shell.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake pie on cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 50 minutes longer.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: white clam sauce
