directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Remove garlic.
Stir in flour, clam juice, salt, pepper and parsley. Simmer 10 minutes. Add clams and heat.
Combine sauce with pasta.
Grate Parmesan cheese and toss to coat noodles.
Garnish with fresh parsley and cheese sprinkled on top.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion, chiles, milk and soups.
Put 2 to 4 Tbsp. chicken broth into bottom of casserole, then layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese, using half each time until cheese finishes on top.
Cover, refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix Crisco oil with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Dip chicken pieces in oil.
Roll in crumb mixture. Bake on foil lined cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, juice of lemon, and salt in double boiler; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Let stand for 1 hour or longer before serving.

title: quick focaccia breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain tomatoes, reserving oil. Finely snip tomatoes.
In bowl, combine tomatoes, cheese, rosemary, pepper, 2 teaspoons of the reserved oil, and the water.
Set aside.
Unroll pizza dough.
On floured surface roll dough into a 10 x 8 inch rectangle.
Spread tomato mixture crosswise over half the dough.
Fold the plan half of dough over filling and press lightly.
Cut folded dough lengthwise into ten 1/2 inch strips. Twist each strip two or three times and place 1 inch apart on a lightly grease baking sheet.
Bake 12 -
15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nancy's cream cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, cream cheese, onion, tomato sauce and eggs. Add just enough bread crumbs to absorb excess moisture. Mix well. Add celery, seasoning and vegetables. Cook until firm or slightly well browned at 350°.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: diabetic white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water. Combine Sugar Twin, flour, salt and milk. Cool until thick. Add softened gelatine, stirring until dissolved. Add vanilla and almond extract. Chill. Whip Dream Whip and fold in gelatine mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold them into the mixture carefully. Fold in coconut. Chill until firm. Garnish with coconut and gumdrops.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes; combine with butter and other ingredients.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: date roll
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil (soft ball stage).
Add dates.
Take from fire and beat until creamy.
When cool, add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until real stiff.
Turn out on cloth rung out of water and roll.
Cut into pieces and enjoy.

title: southern biscuit muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in oleo. Stir in milk.
Drop in muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: party tidbits
directions: In
a
6-quart	Dutch
oven, melt butter over low heat. Add soy sauce, seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt; stir.
Add	noodles,
pretzels, wheat and rice squares, pecans and
cashews;
mix well.
Heat, covered, over low heat for	15 minutes;
stir
occasionally.
Remove
cover; heat an additional 15 minutes to crisp tidbits.
Serve warm or cooled. Makes 10 cups of tidbits.

title: blue ribbon recipe for a good child
directions: Take one child (any age), mix well with unconditional love, endless patience, interest and guidance.
Glaze with courage and lots of self-esteem.
Sprinkle with fun and laughter.
Continue to stir these ingredients until the child is fully raised and there will be enough love and goodness to serve the entire world.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add buttermilk, soda and nuts. Mix well. Add eggs and bananas. Mix. Add flour, baking powder and nuts. Mix well. Spray loaf pan with Pam. Can use 5 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Serve with the following condiments: chopped peanuts, bacon (crumbled), chopped eggs, green onions, raisins, coconut and chutney.
Serve with Herb Bread.

title: beef almondine
directions: Brown meat, drain, add salt, onion, pimento, mushrooms, celery, green pepper, soy sauce, water and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and cook until vegetables are tender. Combine noodles and sour cream with ground meat and vegetables. Pour into a greased 2 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Top with almonds. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: grandma's jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well.
In another bowl, combine buttermilk and jam.
In a third bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with combined dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Once all ingredients are mixed well, add nuts, apple and raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 greased 9 inch cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good with homemade caramel icing.

title: tamale casserole with corn chips
directions: In 2 tablespoons olive oil, brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except corn chips.
Heat to boiling. Stir in chips; remove from heat and cool.
Put in a casserole and top with 1 1/2 cups grated American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well; add oats and vanilla.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: perky punch(hot)
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients into a 50-cup percolator; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place next 3 ingredients in percolator basket.
Percolate as for coffee.
Serve hot.

title: hawaiian pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in Reynolds Brown-in-Bag regular size 10 x 16-inch bag (or large).
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season roast with ginger, salt and garlic powder.
Quarter pineapple slices.
Secure to roast with toothpicks.
Combine reserved syrup and soy sauce in bag and turn bag to mix.
Place roast in bag.
Close with twist tie.
Make 6 slits in top.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Make rice according to package directions; cool.
Beat eggs together and scramble in a pan with a little oil, set aside in a dish.
Heat approximately 3 tablespoons oil until hot in a large frying pan; add cooled rice* and stir until well coated with oil. Heat through.
Add onions and scrambled eggs to rice; mix well. Add soy sauce and sugar to rice mixture and mix well.
Heat through.

title: strawberry oat bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix milk, strawberry juice, strawberries, egg whites and oil in bowl or blender. Combine with dry ingredients and mix.
Line muffin cups and fill with batter.
Bake 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: beef-olive cheese ball
directions: Combine margarine and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients, except nuts.
Shape into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Serve with crackers and celery sticks.

title: orange sherbet fluff
directions: Mix gelatin using only half as much water. Blend oranges in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator to set. Garnish with orange slices and cherries.

title: minted cherry tomatoes
directions: Toss tomatoes with oil, sugar and herbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Toss green onions with tomato mixture.
Use leftover in sauces and soups.
Serve with toothpicks for relish tray.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk until smooth.
Add vanilla and peanut butter, mixing until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine all together.
Put in unbaked crust; bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit shell salad
directions: Prepare shells according to directions; drain.
In a small bowl, blend yogurt and orange juice.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture; toss to coat.
Cover. Chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together next 3 ingredients and add oatmeal mixture, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven in loaf pan.

title: date bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Pat half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turkey hash
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Add turkey, broth, soup, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot homemade biscuits.

title: cherry blossoms(mini cheesecakes)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of paper lined muffin tins. Fill 2/3 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
They will look pale and sunken after cooling.
When cool, remove paper liners.
Top with a spoonful of pie filling.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt chips and oleo. Blend in sugar, eggs and nuts. Can add coconut to one or both, if desired. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Place shield around edges. Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes. Keep refrigerated.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and toss with butter.
Saute onion and burger in oil.
Add garlic salt, salt and mushroom soup; blend well.
Combine noodles with burger mixture.
Cover with buttered croutons.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Mix all ingredients except Stove Top.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cook Stove Top as directed.
Put on top of mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Add onion, tomato and Zesty Italian; stir well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Sprinkle Mrs. Dash on top when served.

title: sissy's salsa
directions: Crush the peppercorn, dice the tomatoes, mince the onion fine, dice the Serrano peppers, then add tomatoes, onion and Serranos and mash them together.
Cut the lemons in fourths and squeeze the juice every once in a while.
Mash the cilantro leaves in with it. Add salt and pepper for your taste.

title: orange chiffon
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Whip with mixer until lighter color and frothy.
Slowly beat in the pint of ice cream. (Let stand when you first start making this, so that it will soften just a little.)
Add Cool Whip.
Save about 16 to 20 of the orange slices, after you drain them.
Fold in the other orange pieces, then use the remaining 16 to 20 to decorate the top.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Slice mushrooms into strips, cut carrots and potatoes into pieces.
Combine ham, mushrooms, carrots, potatoes, sauerkraut, onion and
caraway seed into 8 cups water.
Simmer for 1 hour. Brown the minced onion in bacon fat, thicken with flour.
Add to soup, stirring constantly . Add sauerkraut juice .
Simmer another 15 minutes.
By this time, the meat has fallen off the meat bone. Remove the bone and serve.

title: four layer delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with pecans and flour. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: countryside potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes in package 10 to 12 minutes or until steaming hot, turning package over once.
Empty potatoes into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add milk, salt and parsley.
Mix with fork.
Cut oleo into pieces and place on potatoes.
Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Stir mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Microwave at 1/2 power, uncovered, 8 to 9 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no boil da' noodles vegie lasagne
directions: Spread layer of sauce in a baking dish.
Place a layer of noodles.
Mix cheeses together and place a layer of noodles, followed by a layer of lightly steamed vegetables (water squeezed out).
Repeat layers.
Add remaining sauce and press layers down. Bake at 400° for 55 minutes, covered with foil.

title: bacon and egg lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne to desired doneness.
Drain.
Rinse in hot water. In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Reserve 1/3 cup drippings.
Set bacon aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth and bubbly. Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish. Spoon a small amount of sauce in pan, then layer the noodles, bacon, sauce, eggs and Swiss cheese.
Try for a total of three layers.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine persimmon pulp, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to persimmon mixture alternately with a combination of milk and baking soda.
Use a pastry brush to coat baking pan well with melted butter.
Stir remaining butter into 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add to combined remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly, mixing well.
Place in a 3-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Or, lightly stuff dressing into body cavity and neck region of a 16 to 18 pound turkey and roast according to standard roasting directions.

title: fall-a-part tender slow-roast pork(8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°; reduce to 200° for 4 hours or slow cook in crock-pot 8 hours.

title: fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Blend ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes for a 10-inch tube pan, 45 to 50 minutes for two 8-inch round pans, 40 to 45 minutes for two 9-inch round pans and 50 to 55 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool tube cake 25 minutes. Cool others 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add scalded milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over boiling water until thickened.
Cool; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in jello; let stand until cold.
Stir in nuts and Cool Whip until well mixed, then add buttermilk.
Let stand 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. grease a 15 X 10 baking pan. In a small bowl, combine flour soda, and salt, set aside. In a large bowl combine butter, sugars, and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chips and nuts. spread into baking pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Cool. Cut into 2 inch squares. Makes 35.

title: savory chicken bundles
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter; add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onions, almonds, mushrooms and lemon pepper.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles and seal together.
Spoon in chicken mixture. Close rolls by bringing edges together in the center.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, melt butter and brown meat.
Stir in soup mix, beans, ketchup, water and mustard; pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: big mac "secret sauce"
directions: Combine Miracle Whip with French dressing.
Add the sweet pickle relish, sugar, pepper and the onion.
Blend well using a fork instead of a mixer.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and butter flavoring.
Stir and pour over popcorn.
Put on greased sheet and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir at 15 minute intervals. Store in tight containers.

title: reese's pieces
directions: Melt butter and cool slightly.
In bowl, mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and cracker crumbs, then add butter.
Mix well by hand, not beaters.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put oysters in pan; salt and pepper.
Cook until oysters begin to curl.
Put in the butter until it melts.
Cook slowly about 10 minutes; set off stove and add milk.
Heat slowly until almost to a boil.
Turn down and cook slowly but don't let come to a boil.

title: luscious choco-cherry cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease
and
flour
Bundt pan. Combine flour,
sugar,
soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla;
mix
well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour. Cool cake in pan for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Sift
powdered
sugar
on
top and garnish top of cake and plate with mint leaves.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus in casserole.
Mix soup, asparagus liquid, salt and pepper; pour over asparagus.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over asparagus.
Top with grated cheese and almonds.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or
at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill a few hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: mooseburger chop suey
directions: Cut celery, pepper and onion in thin slices.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet and cook onion, celery, pepper and meat over very high heat.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to meat mixture.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar, pepper, soy sauce and cold water to a smooth paste.
Add to meat mixture and stir thoroughly.
Drain vegetables well and mix into meat mixture.
Heat through and serve with rice and Chinese noodles.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and prepare macaroni as directed on the box.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break in small	pieces one angel food cake in bottom of bowl. Spoon 1/2	can
of
pineapple
over
cake.
Spoon	1/2 vanilla pudding
over
cake.
Then	mix strawberries and glaze together and pour
one
half
over
pudding.
Add 1 large Cool Whip on strawberries, then sprinkle with pecans.

title: pork chop-rice bake
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Place rice in bottom of baking dish.
Place pork chops on rice.
Slice tomato, onion and green pepper on top.
Top with bacon drippings.
Add consomme.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Take cover off and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix and bake pizza crust as directed on package, then let cool.
Mix Ranch dressing and sour cream.
Spread on crust. Grate carrots and broccoli.
Layer them on top of dressing, then grate the cheese and put it on top of the vegetables.
I like to keep mine refrigerated, but not too long or the crust gets very soft.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ground meats together; add eggs, then graham cracker crumbs and milk.
Mix well and form into balls with ice cream scoop.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Pour sauce mixture over ham balls and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and baking powder; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add egg, pumpkin and water; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture, mincemeat and nuts. Grease muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli with garlic and red chili pepper
directions: Trim tough ends of broccoli. Use a paring knife to strip peel from stalks.
Depending on the thickness of stalks, cut broccoli in half or quarters, lengthwise.
Cook broccoli in abundant salted, boiling water until just tender (usually 4 to 5 minutes). Drain within a colander.
Combine olive oil, garlic and red chili pepper in large saute pan.
Cook over a low heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until garlic gives off its perfume.
Add broccoli and salt to taste.
Turn stalks gently, occasionally to coat with oil. Serve broccoli hot, warm or at room temperature.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: fried crappie fillets
directions: Drain fish fillets on thick paper towels to drain.
Dip fish in	meal
mixture.	Deep
fry
in
peanut oil until fish floats and
is
golden
brown.
Put paper towels in bottom of paper grocery
bag
and put fried fish on paper towels.
Fold top
of bag down.
Fish will drain and will not get soggy, but will stay warm.

title: d w zingy ketchup
directions: Boil tomato juice until reduced to half of the amount. Combine rest of ingredients and add to juice.
Can be stored one week in refrigerator.

title: chocolate dessert waffles
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening and melt over hot, not boiling, water.
Meanwhile, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat the eggs in a large bowl with mixer until thick and lemon-colored. Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Stir in the flour mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in chocolate mixture thoroughly. Bake in waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.

title: italian flat bread(focaccia)
directions: In a small bowl, mix crust as directed.
Allow to rest.
In a medium bowl, combine mayo and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in all the herbs and spices, blending thoroughly.
Pat the raw dough in your nonstick pan with oiled fingers.
Pat up the sides with your thumb to create a crust.
Prebake the crust by cooking on medium heat on top of the stove for 4 minutes.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cut chicken breasts into medallions. Brown in skillet; sprinkle on 1 tablespoon tarragon; cover.
Flip medallions and brown on other side.
Sprinkle on rest of tarragon and cover.
Stir up drippings and add heavy cream to them.
Low simmer until cream turns light brown.
Serves 4.
Prep time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: cassie's sugar cookies*
directions: Mix ingredients, add flour to form stiff dough (about 5 cups) to roll.
Cut out.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 350° on floured cookie tray.
Do not overbake.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Combine soup and butter in saucepan and stir until melted. Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Fold in grated potatoes.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in bottom of a large coffeemaker.
Place the remaining ingredients in top of large coffeemaker basket.
Let brew.

title: spiced cider
directions: In a large saucepan mix cider, fruit and peels, spices and sugar.
Bring just to a boil.
Immediately turn down heat and let cider simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.

title: steamed asparagus
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a vegetable peeler or knife, if desired.
Arrange asparagus in a steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer to serving dish and drizzle with butter.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy at low speed.
Beat next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown. Immediately press in Kisses or press thumb and fill with jelly.

title: salad dressing
directions: Marinate onions with sugar.
Set aside.
Blend dry ingredients and add corn oil, vinegar and marinated onions.
Blend well and add horseradish.
Let stand at least 1 hour before using.
Makes 3/4 quart.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: orange blossom dessert
directions: Heat 2 cups orange juice, sugar and gelatin in saucepan until gelatin is dissolved.
Mix with remaining 7 cups orange juice, flavoring and nectar.
Whip egg whites until very frothy.
Stir into orange juice mixture.
Pour into 3-quart mold and chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with fresh fruit.

title: patty's pepper salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in pot except peppers.
Let simmer 10 to 20 minutes to semi-liquid.
Add peppers; bring to a boil while stirring.
Boil another 5 minutes.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Put into jars and let seal.
Do not use seeds in top of peppers.
If too thick, add more ketchup or tomato paste.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Make jello using directions on box, eliminating 1/2 cup water. Chill in refrigerator until fairly firm.
Place milk in bowl in freezer until frosty around edges, then whip, adding sugar and vanilla.
Set aside in freezer.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni until done. Heat oil; add onions and meat. After browned, add V-8, chili powder and sugar. Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Mix in macaroni. Garnish with cheese.

title: hawaiian ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Drain off fat and cover with sauce and bake another 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind; blend in fresh yolks.
Turn into cooled crust.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on bag.
While rice is cooking, mix up cans of corn and celery soup.
Add salt and pepper.
When rice is cooked, put in a stick of margarine and let melt.
Add rice and corn in an ovenproof bowl.
Mix and cook until bubbly and top with Cheddar cheese to melt on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread in buttered pan 9-inches (gingerbread or meat loaf pan, it will be quite thick).
Chill until firm.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: "dad's" peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and eggs until lumpy.
Spread mixture over peaches.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in pot. Cook until thick. Cool. Add sliced berries. Pour into pie shell. Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook the meat until it falls apart.
Pull apart or cut up large pieces.
Put in a large pot and add the liquid from the cooked meat. Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer all together for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: In food processor, mix cranberries and orange until well blended.
Add sugar until sweet/tart.
Serve with turkey or white meat chicken.

title: stir-fry squash
directions: Cube squash into bite size pieces. Cut onion and bell pepper into bite size pieces (not small).
Place oil in a large skillet over high heat. When oil is hot, add pepper and onion.

Stir-fry for 1 minute. Add squash. Continue to stir-fry until onion is clear and squash shows signs of being done. Don't overcook. Sprinkle on Mrs. Dash, salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: snowball cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. When cool, punch holes in cake. Top with crushed pineapple. Prepare pudding mix as directed and beat in cream cheese. Pour over crushed pineapple and top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: tamale dip
directions: Unwrap and break up tamales in saucepan; add chili and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted and dip is heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.
The guys love this!

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Just before serving, stir in sour cream to first 3 ingredients.
Coat cucumbers and onion well.
Can add green pepper.
Can use part Ranch dressing for the sour cream.
Serve.

title: oven baked shrimp(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a broiling pan, add all ingredients, except shrimp.
Cook in oven until celery is no longer crunchy, about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Stir and cook until the shrimp turn red, about 15 minutes.
Do not overcook the shrimp.

title: natchitoches buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook to a softball stage or 236°. Remove from heat and cool about 20 minutes. Beat until mixture loses its gloss; drop onto wax paper. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: *Add to batter or add whole ones on top of cake.

title: easy banana pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Slice 1 banana to cover bottom of pie crust.
Pour pudding evenly into crust.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Spoon Cool Whip over pudding to cover top layer.
Top with second banana.
Ready in just minutes.

title: mashed potatoes hot dish
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash them, no lumps.
Add all ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Place in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry dessert squares
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and your choice of flavoring.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Mark 24 squares and put 1 tablespoon filling into each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: one hour buttermilk rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add buttermilk, shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt into mixture; beat until smooth.
Let stand ten minutes.
Roll out; shape as desired.
Place in baking pan.
Let rise for about 30 minutes in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown. Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Melt the butter in the heated milk.
Stir together the remaining ingredients.
Add to hot milk; cook until thick.
More vanilla flavor may be added if you wish.
When ready to serve, whip 1 cup Rich's topping, stir in pudding and fix with graham cracker crumbs.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add milk, water and egg. Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon in hot fat. Cook until golden brown.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Heat vinegar, water, salt, sugar and juice from red beets in a saucepan until the sugar is melted.
In a large jar or bowl, layer the eggs, onion and red beets.
Pour juice over and cover for 12 to 24 hours.
Serve cold.

title: a zooper hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt mustard and jelly slowly (20 minutes).
Cut up hot dogs and add to sauce.
Heat through and serve.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar, buttered bread (diced up) and raisins in a 2-quart casserole dish.
In mixing bowl, blend eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread mixture.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 way through cooking time.
Center should be firm and almost set.
Brown sugar makes sauce on bottom of pan. Serve with the pudding.

title: cheesecake cobbler
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pound cake with melted margarine and 2 eggs.
Spread in pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs (mixture will be gooey).
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or
until brown on top.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well. Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes approximately 3 3/4 cups mix (about 15 six ounce servings).

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruits and pour into baking dish.
Melt margarine. Stir in sugar and spices.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Work in 2 beaten eggs.
Dough will be sticky.
Pat dough into 9 x 13-inch pan, sides and bottom.
Do not grease pan.

title: festive punch
directions: Combine Jell-O and water and dissolve well.
Add pineapple juice, apple juice and 2 small cans lemonade.
Combine sugar and water.
Cook to make a syrup (until sugar dissolves).
Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze in large container about 24 hours.
Before serving, stir to make a slush.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 75 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute hamburger until brown and crumbly and then drain.
Add soup, potatoes, onion, corn and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Lay on raw pieces of chicken. Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
Preheat oven to 300°. Grease one 9-inch square cake pan.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well mixed, scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pour batter into pan and bake 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw mixed vegetables enough to break apart.
Boil until just tender.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish except croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle croutons on top the last 5 minutes.
Use 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orlando coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Combine Coca-Cola Classic and butter in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir.
Mix buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows (this will be thin).

title: tourtiere du canada
directions: In large saucepan, mix ground beef, ground pork, beefy onion mix, nutmeg and allspice.
Add 3/4 cup water; blend thoroughly. Bring to a boil, then cook, covered, over medium heat for 25 minutes.
Stir in flour blended with remaining 1/4 cup water; cook until slightly thickened.

title: broken shrimp jambalaya
directions: Heat oil; add onions, garlic, bell pepper, green onions, sliced smoked sausage, paprika, salt and pepper.
Saute well.
Add shrimp, rice and shrimp stock; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir with a fork.
Replace cover. Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to cream mixture alternately with mashed bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: In a large saucepan, warm cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in shrimp.
Pour into a fondue pot.
Serve with bread cubes for dipping.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
(If refrigerated, bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.)

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook zucchini and onion in boiling salted water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain zucchini mixture well.
In a large bowl combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots. fold in zucchini mixture.
Toss stuffing mix with margarine or butter.
Spread half the stuffing mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon zucchini mixture atop.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake about 25 minutes or until set.
Cool before cutting.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and add buttermilk.
Add flour, sugar, soda and salt which have been mixed together.
Beat well and add shortening.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat until blended and fluffy.
Makes frosting and filling for two 9-inch layers.

title: banana pudding
directions: With electric mixer, blend condensed milk and cream cheese. with and electric mixer, blend pudding and milk.
Add this mixture to the first mixture.
Add Cool Whip, bananas and vanilla wafers. Stir altogether.

title: broccoli bacon quiche(ingredients for 4 servings)
directions: A great light supper summer dish served with garden salad, ice tea and crescent rolls.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and brown lightly in a 10-inch skillet in oil on medium to high with celery and onion (optional), stirring occasionally.
Don't cook it all the way or it will dry out and be tough.
As the chicken is cooking, follow the directions on the Bisquick box for biscuits, but do not cook.
When finished, set aside for later.

title: never tough pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening and salt.
Beat together egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture until mixed well.
Roll out on floured surface.

title: high protein energy bars
directions: Melt together carob chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over sunflower seeds, coconut, wheat germ, nuts and sesame seeds.
Mix well.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and cut.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients with spinach.
Put in casserole dish and top with seasoned bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: appetizer pizza
directions: Saute meat in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add salt and onion; cook until done.
Split muffins.
Spread lightly with butter.
Toast under broiler until lightly browned.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Drain.
Prepare spaghetti sauce according to package directions, using tomato sauce and meat. Combine egg, cottage cheese and salt.
Mix well.
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish, alternate layers of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Melt in pan the butter and cream cheese.
In microwavable bowl, put black olives, artichokes and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour melted cream cheese and butter over olives, artichokes and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix well.
Put the bowl in microwave and heat for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: simple salsa
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Add oysters; let simmer until they curl.
Add half and half and milk.
Simmer (never boil) for 30 minutes and salt and pepper to taste.

title: viola's famous cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
